Commentary: Mir Hamza dishes a length ball, wide of off. It shapes away off the deck which carries well towards the keeper. Good shape to start with.
This is fuller, on leg stump. Tom Latham stays back and clips it behind square on the leg side for a single. Tom Latham and the Kiwis are off the mark.
Hamza serves it full, outside off and gets it to leave the batter. Conway lets it be.
A length ball, wide of off. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper as it stays low and moves away.
Once again Hamza gets it to shape away from the left-hander. Devon Conway watches it sail past him.
A tidy over by Hamza. It is on a length, wide of off. Conway shoulders his arms at it.
Shah starts his spell with a length ball, outside off. Latham leaves it alone for the wicket-keeper.
Touch fuller, angling across the left-hander. Tom Latham isn't tempted with the width on offer.
Fraction shorter, at 140 clicks. This one is in the channel. Tom Latham covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Good length, wide of off, shaping away. Latham has no shot to offer.
Five dots on the trot! This is full and straight on leg. Latham stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Naseem Shah starts his spell with a maiden. It is fuller, outside off. but this time it flies off the deck. Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Full and straight, around middle. Conway blocks it with a straight bat.
A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! It is a length ball that is angled into the batter, it holds its line and ping Conway on his pads. Although, it is going down leg.
Outside off, left alone.
This one is an inswinger, full and on off. Conway defends it with full face.
Much fuller, straying on the pads. Conway stays back and tucks it through the gap at mid-wicket. The batters take a couple. Devon Conway is finally off the mark here.
Full and on off. Conway pats it back to the bowler.
A length ball, close to the batter making Latham play at it. He does so but with an angled bat to backward point.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is a full-lenght ball, on leg stump. Tom Latham keeps his eyes on the ball and flicks it through the gap at mid-wicket for a fine boundary.
Very full, attacking the stumps. Tom Latham presses forward and blocks it into the deck.
Fraction short, outside off. Tom Latham gets it through cover-point off the backfoot. They take two before the fielder cuts it out.
On a length, wide of off. Tom Latham lets it be.
Two dots in a row! Good leave by Latham as this one is shaping away.
FOUR! Devon Conway gets his first boundary. Hamza serves it full and straight, outside off. Devon Conway leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for a boundary.
Perfect response from the bowler. Hamza angles in a length ball, wide of off. This one moves away from the batter. Conway tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, blocked out.
This one comes in from outside off, on a fuller length. Conway blocks it out with full face.
Fuller, on off. Conway closes the face and tucks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Short and punished. Hamza spills a short ball, wide of off. Conway stays back and cuts it through point for a cracking boundary.
It is much fuller, wide of off. Tom Latham gets across and defends it out watchfully.
Another dot now, as Latham leaves this length ball alone.
FOUR! Nicely played. Tom Latham is taking the charge here. It is a short ball, outside off. Tom Latham gets on top of it and cuts it hard through the point region. It races away.
Naseem Shah angles in a full-length ball from 'round the wicket on the pads. Latham tucks it to mid-wicket and crosses for a single.

FOUR! Finds the gap really well. It is overpitched, wide of off. Conway leans in, opens the face of the bat and steers it through backward point. One hand comes off the bat as he hits it but it still has enough legs to reach the fence.
On the pads, flicked into mid-wicket for a single. 10 runs come off the over.
Much fuller and straight, on off. Conway plays it back to the bowler.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Conway tucks it to square on the leg side. One taken.
It is on a length, wide of off, shapes in late. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Another dot now, as this length ball is left alone by the batter.
It is fuller, outside off. Tom Latham strokes it through cover-point for a single.
A length ball, too straight on the pads. Conway flicks it to the leg side.
It is full, shaping in from outside off. Tom Latham steps across and knocks it to mid off.
On off, defended out.
This is angled in around off. on a fuller length. Latham eases it back to the bowler.
This time it is on a length, outside off. Tom Latham defends it to point off the outer half.
Fraction short, on fifth stump. Tom Latham gets on his toes and punches it through cover-point. They take two runs.
Shah serves it full and on off. Latham eases it to mid off.
Flighted and full, around middle and leg. Conway tries to flick but misses and gets pinged on his pads. Abrar Ahmed makes an appeal for lbw but turned down.
It is full and on leg. Conway tucks it to square leg for one.
Abrar Ahmed spills it down leg. Tom Latham stays back and nudges it to square leg for a single.
On leg, tucked to short leg.
It is pushed through quicker and full, on leg. Conway blocks it out.
Abrar Ahmed drags his length back, on middle. Devon Conway goes back and blocks it out with a straight bat.
FOUR! A good-looking shot. It is fuller, wide of off. Tom Latham leans in and drives it through the gap at covers for a fine boundary.
This is outside off, left alone. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
A length ball, on fifth stump. Tom Latham taps it out to safety.
Much fuller and straight. Tom Latham gets behind the line and blocks it out.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Hasan Ali serves it full and down leg. Tom Latham times it to perfections and clips it down to fine leg for four.
Length, outside off, defended out.
Ali serves a length ball, in the channel. Latham covers his stumps and makes the leave.
FOUR! Good use of the feet this time! Ahmed tosses it up on middle. Conway skips down the track, converts it into a full toss and forces it towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Conway punches it to mid on.
Bowls it tad fuller and on middle. Conway fends it from his crease.
SIX! Oh, this is interesting! Good positive cricket from Conway! This is fuller and on middle. Conway shimmies down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and heaves it over long on for a maximum.
Touch shorter and on middle. Conway punches it straight down the ground for a couple.
Comes 'round the wicket and fires it quicker and fuller on middle. Conway defends it off the front foot.
On a good length and around off. Latham defends it towards the point fielder.
Lovely delivery! Short of good length and it is outside off. The ball nips away off the pitch as Latham pushes at it tentatively and gets beaten.
Goes fuller and on off. Latham drives it to mid off for a single.
Bowls it short and around off at 133.3 kph. Conway sways away from the line of the ball.
Serves it on a length, on off at 135 kph. Conway defends it off the front foot.
Lands it on a good length and outside off. Conway lets it go.
Bowls it fuller on off. Tom Latham defends it off the front foot.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Tom Latham works it to square leg for a single.
Tosses it up on off. Conway works it to long on for a single.
Touch shorter and quicker angling into leg. Tom clips it to short fine leg.
Slower through the air on middle. Tom Latham tries to clip it but gets a leading edge towards the off side.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Tom Latham drives it to mid on this time.
Bangs it short and on off. Conway pulls it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and around off. Latham punches it through covers and comes back for the second run as Imam-ul-Haq cuts it off.
Fraction short and angling into off. Latham works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Serves it on a length, on middle. Conway fends it towards the leg side and takes a single.
Lands it on a good length, on off. Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls it on a good length and outside off as Tom Latham makes an easy leave.
Tossed up on off. Conway defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Conway with a solid block again.
In the air but away from the short leg fielder! This is angled into middle from 'round the wicket. Conway tries to defend it but gets the inside edge that goes left of short fine leg.
Touch shorter on middle. Conway clips it to square leg for a single.

Appeal for an LBW but no damage done! Angles it into middle and leg again. Latham shimmies down the track and tries to clip it but misses. He gets hit on the pad but one can't expect umpire to give that out as the batter was way out of his crease.
Flatter and fuller on middle. Latham drives it to mid on this time.
On a good length, on off. Conway fends it off the front foot towards the leg side.
Lands it on a length and angles it on off from 'round the wicket. Conway with a solid block onto the turf.
On a length and around off at 131.8 kph. Conway defends it towards the off side.
Unfortunate for Conway! Overpitched delivery on middle. Conway drives and drives it firmly but the ball goes onto hit the stumps at the bowler's end. A certain boundary saved!
On a good length, on middle. Conway defends it calmly this time.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Conway leaves it alone.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Tosses up on middle. Tom Latham shimmies down the track and drives it down the ground for a boundary.
Angling into leg and flatter. Latham nudges it to short fine leg for a single.
FOUR! Too full and punished! Overpitched delivery on middle. Conway just flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Much better! Drags his length back a bit, on middle. Conway fends it with soft hands towards short leg.
Tossed up delivery on middlle. Conway with a front foot defence.
Touch shorter and on off. Conway goes back and punches it to the bowler.
Back of a length angling into middle and leg. Latham clips it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Serves it a bit fuller and on middle. Latham nudges it to fine leg for a single.
Lands it on a length, on off. Conway fends it from his crease.
On a good length and around off. Conway fends it off the outside half of his blade towards the point fielder.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Conway clips it to square leg calmly.
Inside edge this time! Serves it on a good length on off. The ball shapes in a bit and Conway gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend it.
Tossed up on off. Latham leans forward and defends it solidly.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short and on middle. Tom Latham goes deep in his crease and pulls it towards the mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. Latham drives it to covers for a single.
Serves it fuller and around off. Conway tries to defend it but the ball turns away a bit and beats the outside edge of Conway's blade.
Serves it quicker and flatter on off. Conway blocks it out.
Slower through the air and on off. Conway is well forward to defend it.
Short and wide outside off. Latham cuts it to the cover fielder.

Tom Latham has been given out LBW here! However, he takes the DRS straightaway! The replays roll in and the the UltraEdge shows that Latham has got an inside edge here. So, the decision will be overturned and Latham survives. Coming to the ball - It lands on a length and angling into off. Latham tries to defend it but gets the inside edge that hits Latham high on the pads. The bowler makes a loud appeal but Latham was confident and overturns the decision with a review.
Angles a length delivery on middle and leg. Latham clips it past square leg for a single,
On a good length and on off. Conway fends it back to the bowler.
Touch shorter and around off. Conway punches it to cover-point for a single.
Bit of shape into the batter as Hamza bowls it on a fullish length on off. Latham drives it back to the bowler.
This is aimed on the pads, on a fuller length. Conway flicks it to the leg side.
Full and on off, coming in with the arm. Conway blocks it on his front foot.
Much quicker and fuller, on off. Conway fends it out towards point.
A single now as Devon Conway drives this full delivery to he right of mid off.
It is fuller, on off. Tom Latham gets low and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a couple.
On off, Latham strides forward and blocks it back to the bowler.

Mir Hamza makes a huge appeal for lbw but the umpire is unmoved. Babar Azam gives it a long thought and takes the review eventually. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball, that lands just outside off and nips in off the deck. Devon Conway tries to defend it with straight bat but gets beaten on the inside edge. He gets pinged quite high on the pads. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The ball shows that the ball is bouncing over the wickets. Not a great call by the Pakistani skipper to take the review.
It is full, on the pads, Conway clips it to mid-wicket. They take a single.
Good length, on top of off. Tom Latham shuffles and nudges it to the leg side for one.
FOUR! Top shot. Back of a length, wide outside off. Devon Conway rides the bounce, latches onto it and cuts it past the point fielder for a cracking boundary.
It is full, swinging away a touch. Conway drives it into covers but not in the gap this time.
This one stays low, wide of off. Conway shoulders his arms at it.
It is tossed up, outside off. Latham paddles it down to fine leg for two runs.
Fuller, coming in with the arm. Latham blocks it on his front foot.
Attacking the stumps, on a fuller length. Tom Latham strides and blocks it out.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Loops it up, full and on off. Tom Latham blocks it out solidly.
Quite short, wide of off. Latham hangs back and punches it through point. They cross for a single. A tidy over from Salman comes to an end. The two batters look comfortable out in the middle now.
Easy single! FIFTY IS UP FOR LATHAM! It is a length ball, on off. Tom Latham shuffles and tucks it towards mid-wicket. He crosses for one run.
Much fuller, in the channel. Devon Conway leaves it alone without any hesitation.
Another dot! Hamza dishes a short ball, outside off. Conway cuts it to point but straight to the fielder. He grunts as he does not connect well.

FOUR! Devon Conway moves to 48 now with this boundary. It is full, swinging into Conway around off. Conway takes a step forward and drills it down the ground. Tom Latham has to get out of the way here which results into a boundary at mid on. An exceptional shot, this!
On off, defended out.
Length and outside off. Conway gets behind and defends it out solidly.
It is short, wide outside off. Tom Latham cuts it through point for a single. The stand moves to 100 runs now. Yet another dominating show by the opening pair of New Zealand.
On middle and leg, flicked behind square on the leg side for one.
Loops it up, on off, defended into covers.
Short ball, outside off. Latham cuts it to the man at backward point.
On off, defended out watchfully.
Full and on off. Latham gets on his front foot and blocks it back to the bowler. Just two runs off the over. Salman has been very impactful since coming on.
Conway needs to wait for his half-ton. Shah comes from 'round the wicket and serves it full and on off with pace on. Conway gets across and tucks it to the leg side.

He gets the single now! Conway records his sixth fifty in Test cricket. It is very full and straight, on the pads. Conway flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single. He raises his blade and soaks in applause.
FOUR! Incredible shot! Tom Latham continues on his merry way here. It is a full-length ball, outside off, nipping in a touch. Tom Latham leans in and punches it through covers. It races away.
This is outside off, left alone.
It is quite fuller, sliding down leg. Tom Latham misses his flick. The keeper dives to his right and gathers the ball into his mitts.
A single to end the over! It is full, angled into the batter. Latham eases it towards mid on and crosses.
FOUR! Put away with ease. It is a short ball, outside off. Latham stays back and cuts it hard through covers for a boundary.
Much fuller, on off. Latham opens the face late and guides it down to third man for one.
Outside off, defended to point.
Two dots in a row! This is fuller and on off. Conway uses his feet and pushes it to cover.
Much fuller, attacking the pads, Conway defends it back to the bowler.
Four dots on the trot to end the over! It is full, on middle and leg. Conway comes forward and knocks it to mid on but too close to the fielder there.
FOUR! EDGY! Shah comes from 'round the wicket. He serves it on a length, outside off. Tom Latham gets it past the man at gully off the outside edge. It races away to the fence.
Lands it on a length, on off. Latham fends it off the front foot.
Angles a length delivery on the pads. Latham clips it to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length and around off. Conway dabs it towards the point fielder.
Lands it on a length, around off. Conway blocks it from his crease.
Angles a length delivery on off from 'round the wicket. He goes wide of the crease this time but Conway is calm and condifent in his defence.
A flighted full toss, on off. Latham strokes it through covers for an easy single.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Conway steps across and blocks it out.
Conway comes down the track to the full delivery and clips it towards long on.
This is full and on off. Conway drives it with power down the ground. Agha Salman does well to get a hand on it. They take a single as it goes to mid off.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Flatter, around off. Latham goes back and defends it to cover.
Shah comes from 'round the wicket and serves it full, on off. Conway digs it out watchfully.
Full again, outside off. Conway blocks it into the deck.
Third dot now! It is full, nipping into the batter. Conway tries to flick it away but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Make that four! Fuller, around off. Conway blocks it back to the bowler. Will Shah be able to draw first blood in the next two balls?
Not on this one! This is angled into the batter, on a fuller length. Devon Conway tucks it to mid-wicket quite uncomfortably.
So then, Shah is unable to break the stand here. This is too far enough to bother Conway at all. The batter makes an easy leave. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Serves it fuller and on off to start. Tom Latham with a solid defence off the front foot.
Angles it fuller and quicker on off from 'round the wicket. Tom Latham gets well forward and fends it.
Serves it full and angles it on middle. Tom skips down the track and works it to square leg for a single.
Touch shorter and on middle. Conway goes back and punches it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery this time, on off. Conway with a block off the front foot.
Angles it fuller and touch short of full length. Conway tries to defend but gets an inside edge that loops up a bit in the air in front of short leg.
Serves it on a good length, on off. Latham with a front foot defence towards the off side.
Angles a length delivery on middle at 138.3 kph from 'round the wicket and Latham gets right behind it to block it out.
Just short of good length and around off. Latham punches it to cover-point.
Serves it fuller and on off. Latham drives it to the mid off fielder.
Angles a length delivery on off as he goes wide of the crease but Latham is equal to the task and fends it towards mid on.
Back of a length and around off. Latham dabs it towards the gully region this time.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tossed up on off. Conway takes his front foot forward and drills it down the ground for a boundary.
Shortish and angling into leg. Conway clips it to short fine leg.
Slower through the air, on off. Conway drives it wide of mid off for an easy single.
Touch shorter and on middle. Latham goes deep in his crease and punches it to long on for a single.
Fires it flatter and quicker on off. Conway pushes it towards the off side without much fuss.

Angles it on the pads. Conway misses his glance as the ball goes off his pads towards short fine leg. The batters run for a leg bye and completes it easily even though the fielder at short fine leg fires a direct hit at the bowler's end.
Lands it on a length, on off. The ball straightens after pitching and Conway defends it onto the turf.
Bit of reverse swing here! Lands it on a length, on off. Some shape away from the batter and Conway blocks it back to the bowler.
Fullish length and on off. Conway pushes it back to the bowler.
Pitches it on a good length and it is outside off. The ball comes in to Conway but it is still outside off and Conway leaves it easily.
Lands a length delivery, outside off and Conway leaves it alone again. Bit of stare from Shah to Conway!

Big appeal for LBW from the bowler but it is clearly going down leg. A length delivery angling into leg from 'round the wicket. Conway tries to clip it but misses and gets hit on the pads. A big appeal follows but the umpire is not interested.
A flatter delivery on middle. Latham clips it to backward square leg for a single.
Slower through the air and on off. Conway fends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Poor line and punished! This is angled into the pads and it is easy for Conway as he clips it towards the backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Bit quicker and fuller on off. Conway pushes it to covers.
Touch shorter and angling into middle. Conway goes deep in his crease and punches it down the ground for a single.
Fires it flatter and quicker on middle. Tom Latham punches it to mid on for a single.

OUT! LBW! Oh, the reverse-swing finally works! Naseem Shah strikes and gets a big wicket of Tom Latham! The young man is pumped up and rightly so, he deserves this wicket as he created something with his reverse-swing here when nothing was going right for Pakistan. He serves it on a fullish length and angles it on middle and leg from 'round the wicket. Latham tries to flick it but loses his balance and misses it to get hit on the pads. Naseem Shah makes a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger this time. Latham has a long discussion with his opening partner but finally decides against taking the DRS. He departs for a well-made fifty!
Howout: lbw b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Serves it on a good length and outside off. Shapes in a bit and Kane Williamson leaves it.
On a good length, on off. Kane Williamson blocks it onto the turf.
A length ball, nipping in from outside off. Kane Williamson gets inside and tucks it to the leg side.
Serves it just short of good length and around off at 141.3 kph. Kane Williamson fends it towards the off side.
Nicely bowled again! Good reverse again as he lands it on a good length, on off. The ball shapes in a bit and Kane Williamson defends it with a straight blade back to the bowler.
Slower through the air, on off. Conway with a front foot defence now.
Touch shorter and on middle. Conway goes deep in his crease and works it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Conway has played Abrar Ahmed quite well today! Driving length, around off. Conway drives and drives it past mid off for a boundary,
Nice timing again! Bowls it fuller and on middle. Conway flicks it through mid-wicket. Ali runs to his right in the deep and dives to stop it inside the fence. Two taken.
Touch shorter and around off. Conway punches it through the cover region for a couple.
Angles a quicker and flatter delivery on the pads. Conway tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards the leg side. A leg bye is taken.
A fullish delivery on middle. Conway pushes it back to the bowler.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Conway clips it to deep backward square leg for a couple.
Angles another delivery on middle at 140.7 kph. Conway fends it back to the bowler.
Serves it on a fullish length and drifts on the pads. Conway calmly clips it past square leg and the batters take three.

Lovely delivery! Shah with a perfect good-length delivery, outside off. Kane Williamson initially sets up to push at it but the ball shapes away and Kane Williamson just about manages to get his bat away from the line of the ball at the last moment.
Back of a length and around off. Kane Williamson dabs it towards the point fielder.
Bowls it fuller and on off. Conway drives it through the extra-cover region for a couple.
Bowls it flatter and on middle at 86.8 kph. Conway blocks it out.
Touch shorter and on leg. Conway clips it to deep square leg for a single.

Big appeal for LBW but it is going down leg. Ahmed fires it quicker and it turns in sharply to Williamson. He shimmies down the track and tries to work it towards the leg side but gets hit on the pads. An appeal follows but no damage done.

FOUR! This is poor from Abrar Ahmed! Shortish and outside off. Kane Williamson goes deep in his crease and chops it through the point region where Hasan Ali chases it and puts in a slide near the fence to stop it but his right leg touches the ropes and it is a boundary. Abrar Ahmed needs to be more consistent with his length here.
Tossed up on off. Williamson drives it to mid off for a single.
Serves a fullish delivery with a shape away from the batter. Kane Williamson drives it to covers.
FOUR! Nice timing from Williamson! A half-volley, outside off. Williamson leans forward and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Pulls his length back a bit, outside off. Williamson leaves it alone.
On a good length again but wider outside off and Kane Williamson makes an easy leave.
Back of a length and outside off at 132.9 kph. Williamson lets it go. Ali needs to make him play more.
A harmless length delivery, outside off and Kane Williamson is just happy to let it go.
FOUR! Good use of the wrists this time. It is looped up, full and on leg. Conway uses his feet and clips it through mid-wicket for a fine boundary. Conway gets into his 80s.
Abrar Ahmed overcompensates this time with a short ball, outside off. Conway stays back and cuts it hard through cover-point. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it out.

FOUR! Runs are coming in thick and fast here. Abrar Ahmed now spills this down leg. Kane Williamson gets low and tries to sweep. He gets a fine tickle on it and drags it fine. It races away to the fine leg fence.
Fuller and on off, blocked out solidly.
Tossed up, on off. Kane Williamson is solid in his defense.
Pushed through on off, Kane Williamson gets on his front foot and blocks it into the deck.
Ali comes 'round the wicket and angles it in, full and on off. Good line this time from the seamer. Devon Conway gets across a bit and defends it out.
Much fuller on off, Devon Conway gets behind and blocks it to the leg side. No ball called for overstepping this time.
This is full, on middle and leg. Conway tries to flick but gets it on his pads off the inner half. Another no ball, as Ali oversteps yet again.
Ali dishes a hard-length delivery, outside off. Conway defends it out solidly.
Length, on middle and leg. Conway gets across and tucks it to mid-wicket.
It is full, straying on the pads, Conway flicks it to deep square leg. Naseem Shah is quick to get to the ball and only allows a single.
Ali now dishes an inswinger, on a fuller length, on off. Kane Williamson digs it out in time.

This is too full. Kane Williamson flicks it off his pads to deep square leg. The batters take two quite comfortably. Some positive signs for Ali, he will surely grow into his spell and try to cause some damage.
This is tossed up, full and on middle. Devon Conway blocks it back to the bowler.
Floats it up, around leg. Conway tucks it besides short leg.
Devon Conway rotates the strike now as he flicks this full delivery to deep square leg.
A dot now! Loops it up, full and outside off. Kane Williamson strides forward and fends it out.
Kane Williamson uses his feet this time and flicks this full delivery to the man at mid on.
A quite tidy over from Abrar Ahmed under pressure. Just a single off the over. This is full, on middle and leg. Kane Williamson nudges it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on fourth stump. Blocked.
It is a good-length ball, on top of off. Conway defends it out solidly.

DROPPED! How costly will this turn out to be? A lucky escape for Devon Conway this time. It is a full-length ball, outside off. Devon Conway tries to go for the booming drive but only gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the man at first slip but it is always dying on him. The fielder there gets low in front of him but is unable to gather it. A huge chance goes abegging.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Conway flicks this through mid-wicket for three runs now.
Back of a length, on fourth stump. Kane Williamson shuffles and works this towards mid on. They take a single.
A length ball, outside off. Conway defends it out watchfully.
Pitches it up, around off. Kane Williamson drives it towards mid off.
Loops it up, outside off, it turns away a touch. Kane Williamson does not bother.
This one turns in, on a shorter length from off. Kane Williamson blocks it to the leg side.
Short once again, outside off. Kane Williamson knocks it to the cover region.
On off, Kane Williamson defends it out watchfully.
Kane Williamson offers full face of the bat this time to this full delivery, on middle and leg. A maiden over for Abrar Ahmed his first one of the day.
Full length, outside off, driven to short extra cover.

FOUR! A fortunate boundary this time. It is a full-length ball, wide outside off. Devon Conway goes for a full-blooded drive, although he gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball carries to the right of the man at gully. The fielder there makes a goal-keeper like dive to his right, gets both hands on it but the power let it through his finger and into the boundary at third man.
Length ball, on off, defended out.
This is outside off. Devon Conway lets it through.
Devon Conway defends this length ball quite comfortably.
Much fuller, on off. Conway drives it to mid on.
Tosses it up, on off. Kane Williamson defends it on his front foot,
It is full, sliding down leg. Kane Williamson sweeps it behind square o the leg side.
This is short, outside off. Kane Williamson punches it to covers.
It is full and on off. It grips and turns away a touch. Kane Williamson gets it to slip off the outer half.
On off, defended into the deck.
Floats it up, around off. Kane Williamson smothers it to covers.
A length ball, outside off. Conway taps it to point.
Ali serves it on a length this time, wide of off. Conway has no shot to offer.
It is full, outside off. Devon Conway drives it towards sweeper cover for one run.
It is full, straying on the pads, Kane Williamson nudges it to the leg side.
A length ball, attacking the off stump. Kane Williamson blocks it out firmly.
It is full, swinging into the pads. Williamson stays back to clip this through mid-wicket for a single.
Short ball, outside off. Kane Williamson pushes it to covers.
Quite short, around off. Kane Williamson flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off. Kane Williamson gets on his front foot to defend it out.
FOUR! Up and over! It is tossed up, full and on off. Kane Williamson gets down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for four runs.
Kane Williamson goes back to this short delivery and defends it out to covers.
Fuller and on off. Kane Williamson pushes it back to the bowler with soft hands.

A great start to the spell by Hamza now. It is a length ball, outside off, tailing back into the batter with some extra bounce. Devon Conway tries to block it out but misses and gets pinged high on his pads.
Mir Hamza spills this one down leg. Devon Conway is unable to get near the ball.
This is full, straying on the pads, Conway gets it out off his pads. Mir Hamza makes an appeal for lbw but turned down. Meanwhile, the batters collect a leg bye.
Length, on fifth stump. Kane Williamson defends it out watchfully.
Much fuller, wide of off, shaping away. Kane Williamson lets it be.
Good length, outside off. Kane Williamson shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Conway moves onto 98 now! Drifts on the pads and it is flatter too. Conway just tucks it off his pads and the ball runs away towards the fine leg fence.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Conway clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Goes wide of the crease and  tosses it up on off. Kane Williamson gets well forward and blocks it out.
Touch shorter and on off. Williamson works it to short leg.
On the shorter side, on off. Williamson blocks it off the back foot.
Fires it quicker and on middle. Kane Williamson fends it solidly yet again.

There it is...4th Test century for Devon Conway! This man just continues to score runs across formats. His hunger for runs is just unbelievable and  surely he would like to convert this into a huge score. A fuller delivery on middle. Conway flicks it through mid-wicket and the batters take three.

FOUR! Placement and class from Williamson! Back of a length and around off. Williamson dabs it in the gap behind square on the off side as the ball races away towards the third man fence for a boundary.
On a length and outside off. Williamson is happy to let it go.
Serves it on a good length again, on off. Williamson blocks it right under his eyes.
Just short of good length and it is angled across the right-hander. Williamson lets it go calmly.
On a good length and it is outside off. Kane Williamson with an easy leave again.
Tossed up nicely on off. Conway fends it off the front foot nicely.
Bit quicker and on middle. Conway clips it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Fires it on middle. Williamson clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Pulls his length back a bit, on middle. Conway defends it off the inside half of his blade towards square leg for a single.
Overpitched delivery, around off. Williamson drives and drives it through covers for a couple.
Fraction short and flatter on middle. Williamson works it to the square leg fielder.
Back of a length and angling into middle. Conway works it to mid-wicket this time.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Shortish and provides a bit of width as well as Conway cuts and does so in the gap through the backward point region for a boundary.
Bowls a fullish delivery on off. Conway drives it straight to the mid off fielder.
On a good length and it is outside off. Conway lets it go.
On a length and outside off at 129.2 kph. Conway leaves it alone.
Oh, another one of those inside edges from Conway! This is a fullish delivery and outside off. Conway goes for a big booming drive but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Bowls it fuller and on off at 87.3 kph. Williamson fends it off the front foot.
Slowers his pace a bit on middle. Williamson fends it off the front foot.
This is flatter and quicker, outside off. Williamson leaves it alone.
Consistent length and line now from Ahmed. This is fuller and on off. Williamson fends it solidly off the front foot.
Bowls it bit quicker and outside off. Williamson leans forward and blocks it out.
A quicker and fuller on off. Kane Williamson is just happy to block it out.
Serves it on a length, on middle. Conway works it to the mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Great timing from Conway again! Hamza drfits on the pads as he bowls it fuller in length again. Conway flicks and does so in the gap through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Shorter in length, on off. Conway punches it to the mid off fielder.
On a length and outside off. Conway punches it to the cover fielder.
Lands it on a length, on off. Conway covers his off stump and blocks it out.
Serves it fuller and on middle. It shapes in a bit and Conway works itt through mid-wicket for a couple.
Shortish and on off. Williamson goes back and pushes it to mid on.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Williamson works it wide of mid on for a single.

FOUR! Wow! What a shot from Devon Conway! This is touch shorter and on off. Nothing much wrong in this delivery but Conway goes deep in his crease and just punches it with great timing through covers for a boundary.
Tosses it up and on off. Conway with a front foot defence this time.
Slower through the air again, on off. Conway fends it onto the turf with soft hands.
Pulls his length back, on middle. Conway punches it to long on for a single.
Slower through the air, on middle. Conway fends it off the front foot.
Goes fuller and around off. Conway drives it to the cover fielder.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off. Conway with a front foot defence.
Overpitched delivery on off. Conway drives it to long off for a single.
Bowls it quicker and fuller on off. Williamson works it to short leg.
Fraction short and on off. Williamson goes back and pushes it towards the short mid-wicket fielder. It shall be Tea on Day 1!
Starts off with a tossed up delivery on off. Conway with a solid front foot defence.
Angles it on leg and Conway misses his flick shot to get hit on the pads. The ball deflects towards short fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
Touch shorter and on middle. Williamson works it through nid-wicket and they come back for three runs.
Fires it quicker and flatter on middle. Conway blocks it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker and on middle. Conway drives it to the mid on fielder.
Slower through the air, on off. Conway fends it with soft hands again.
Starts off with a peach of a delivery! Serves it on a good length and around off. The ball shapes away a bit and the ball beats the outside edge of Williamson's blade as he tries to defend it.
Back of a length and around off. Williamson punches it to covers for a single.
Angles a length delivery on middle from 'round the wicket. Conway fends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side for a single.
Serves it on a good length and around off. Williamson fends it onto the turf.
Beautifully bowled again! Lands it on a good length and around off. Tha ball shapes away nicely and Williamson keeps his bat cleverly inside the line of the ball to let it go.
Serves it on a length, on off. Williamson fends it towards the leg side.
This is full, coming in with the arm. Devon Conway prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Slower through the air this time, full and on off. Conway drives it to cover.
This full delivery is driven past mid off for an easy single.
Touch short, outside off. Kane Williamson taps it to covers.
This is on the pads, nudged to square leg for one.
This is tossed up, outside off. Conway blocks it away.
It is a goodlength ball, outside off. Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
This a length ball that nips in from outside off. Kane Williamson nudges it to mid-wicket off his pads.
A length ball, in the channel. Kane Williamson blocks it late towards the slip cordon.
Naseem Shah dishes a length ball, tailing into the batter. Kane Williamson gets inside and cips it to mid-wicket.
Shah goes full and outside off. Kane Williamson defends it to gully off the outer half.
It is full, wide of off, shaping away. Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
On off, defended back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Devon Conway gets a faint edge on this one and has to depart after a really good knock He will be very disappointed with the way he gave away his wicket here. Agha Salman has brought some hope back into the Pakistan dressing room. It is a loopy delivery, outside off. It grips and turns away. Devon Conway is unsure of how to deal with the delivery and ends up hanging his blade away from his body. The ball takes the faintest of edges and Sarfaraz Ahmed makes no mistake behind the sticks.
Howout: c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Agha Salman

Commentary: On off, blocked out watchfully.
FOUR! Henry Nicholls gets off the mark with a boundary here. It is full, on middle and leg. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps it fine. The ball races to the fine leg fence.
Looped up, on off, Henry Nicholls blocks it out.
This is pushed through, on middle. Henry Nicholls presses forward and blocks it with full face. A successful over from Agha Salman comes to an end.
It is full, down the leg side. Kane Williamson clips it to deep mid-wicket for two runs.
An outswinging full-length delivery, on off. Kane Williamson pats it back to the bowler.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Kane Williamson leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Kane Williamson blocks it into the deck.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one bites the dust. This is turning out to be a golden period for Pakistan. The Kiwis now lose their third wicket. Naseem Shah serves a length ball, in the channel and gets it to shape away off the deck. Kane Williamson is drawn into it and tries to block it away without any foot movement. The ball takes a thick outside edge and flies to the right of the keeper. Sarfaraz Ahmed there dives to his right to take a solid catch.
Howout: c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Naseem Shah

Commentary: Full length, on off, defended out watchfully.
Tossed up, on off, blocked away.
It is full and on off. Henry Nicholls works it to mid on.
FOUR! It is a short ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls stands tall and cuts it hard through point for a boundary.
Henry Nicholls clips this full ball to square leg for one.
Daryl Mitchell comes down the track to this full delivery and flicks it to long on for a single.
This is tossed up, outside off. It flies off the deck. Henry Nicholls tries to go after it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Lands it on a good length and on off. Mitchell fends it off the front foot. Shah gets some good movement away from the right-hander again here.
A fullish delivery on off. Mitchell drives it to mid off and takes a single.
On a good length and it is way outside off. Henry Nicholls lets it go.
Serves it a bit fuller and angles it on middle from 'round the wicket. Nicholls clips it to the mid-wicket fielder.
On a length, on off. Henry Nicholls covers the line of the ball and blocks it out.
Shortish and it is outside off. The ball shapes away this time and Henry Nicholls tries to cut it but misses.
Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell fends it off the front foot.
Touch shorter and on off. Daryl Mitchell defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off. Daryl Mitchell reverse-sweeps it to the point fielder.
Touch on the shorter side, on middle. Daryl Mitchell punches it to long on for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Henry Nicholls gets well forward to block it.
On the shorter side, on off. Henry Nicholls punches it to covers for a single.
On a good length, on off from 'round the wicket. Henry Nicholls presses forward to defend it.
Serves it on a good length and it is outside off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
FOUR! Bit short and width offered as well and Henry Nicholls punishes it. He goes deep in his crease and cuts it through backward point for a boundary. Good shot!

Angles a length delivery, around off. Henry Nicholls fends it towards backward point where Imam-ul-Haq dives to stop it. That creates misunderstanding between the batters as Mitchell is ball-watching and hesitates to take a single initially. However, he does respond to his partner eventually and the batters take a single as Imam-ul-Haq misses his shy at the batter's end.
Fuller and on middle. Daryl Mitchell drives it back to the bowler.

Serves it nice and full shaping into the batter. Daryl Mitchell tries to flick it away but misses to get hit on the pads. Shah goes down in appeal but it is clearly drifting down leg and he also knows it.
On middle and flatter. Henry Nicholls clips it to square leg for a single.
Bowls it quicker and on middle. Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Turning into middle and leg. Daryl Mitchell works it to short leg.
Tossed up on middle. Daryl Mitchell clips it to the mid-wicket fielder.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! Agha Salman gets his second wicket and Pakistan are turning it on after Tea! This is a classical off-spinner's wicket. Tosses it up on off. Daryl Mitchell leans forward to work it towards the leg side. However, the ball turns into the batter and goes through the gap between bat and pad to knock over the stumps.The fifth bowler is doing the trick for Pakistan and they would like to capitalize on this opening now.
Howout: b Agha Salman

Commentary: Loopy delivery on off. Tom Blundell fends it off the inside half of his blade towards short leg.
A fuller delivery, around off. Henry Nicholls drives it to the cover fielder.
On a good length, around off. Henry Nicholls fends it to the short cover fielder.
Back of a length, on middle. Henry Nicholls clips it to the mid-wicket fielder.
On a good length and around off. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on off. Henry Nicholls blocks it calmly.

Serves it on a length, on middle. Henry Nicholls defends it left of the bowler and Hasan Ali dives to his left, stops it and ends up showing his antics to add some drama and humour to the proceedings.
Tossed up on middle. Tom Blundell fends it off the front foot calmly.
Goes fuller and on middle again. Tom Blundell drives it to mid on for a single.
Short ad on off. Henry Nicholls knocks it to the off side but it hits silly point on its way.
A single now as this is swept behind square leg.
On off, flicked past short leg.
Full and on off. Tom Blundell presses forward and defends it solidly. Just two runs off it. Pakistan have done really well to put a lid over the run rate so far in the final session.
Fuller in length, on off. Henry Nicholls taps it to cover.
Ali serves it on a length, outside off. This one shapes away a touch. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Three dots in a row! This is tailing into the batter from outside off on a fuller length. Henry Nicholls shuffle and flicks it towards mid on.
It is overpitched, wide outside off. Henry Nicholls times his drive well towards covers but only get a single as the fielder there dives to his right to make a sharp stop.
Hasan Ali fires in a yorker-length delivery, on middle and leg, tailing back into the batter. Tom Blundell digs it out in time.
Full, on the pads, Tom Blundell nudges it to the leg side.
Flatter and on off. Henry Nicholls blocks it from his crease.
Salman drags his length back, outside off. Henry Nicholls waits for it and cuts it late to backward point.
On middle and leg, clipped to short leg.
Short and outside off, Defended.
Pushed through quicker, full and on leg. Henry Nicholls goes back and defends it firmly.
Loops it up, wide of off. Henry Nicholls prods across and lets it be.
It is full, swinging into the batter. Tom Blundell stays back and flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Ali goes full again, tailing into the batter from outside off. Tom Blundell flicks it behind square on the leg side for two runs.
Tom Blundell flicks it to mid-wicket off his pads.
Length, around off, punched into the off side.
This is a length ball, that lands on outside off and nips in off the deck. Tom Blundell nudges it to the leg side.
Ali serves an inswinging delivery, full and on off. Tom Blundell dabs it out to point.
Flighted and on off, pushed to covers.
On leg, clipped to mid-wicket.
This is tossed up, on leg. Henry Nicholls flicks it past mid-wicket for one run.
Tom Blundell comes down the track and clips this full ball to mid on.
A single now as this is worked to mid on.
This is full and on off. Henry Nicholls defends it watchfully.
A length ball, going down leg. Blundell flicks it to fine leg for a single.
Ali serves it on a length, Henry Nicholls gets pinged on his pads as he fails to block it away.
On a good length and it is angled across the left hander. Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on middle. Henry Nicholls clips it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Bangs it short and on off. Henry Nicholls tries to pull it but misses. The ball hits his shoulders and deflects towards the off side.
Back of a length and around off. Henry Nicholls dabs it towards the point fielder.
FOUR! Lovely use of the feet! Tossed up on off. Tom Blundell shimmies down the track and drills it down the ground for a boundary.
This is flatter and quicker down the leg side. Tom Blundell lets it go.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Tom Blundell drives it to long on for a single.
Fires it quicker and flatter on off. Henry Nicholls fends it towards the off side.
Slower through the air, on off. Henry Nicholls leans forward and fends it out.
Tosses this up and on off. Henry Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Fires it quicker and down the leg side. Tom Blundell lets it go.
Goes fuller and on middle. Tom Blundell works it to mid-wicket.
Touch shorter and on off. Tom Blundell punches it to the cover fielder.
Slower through the air on leg. Tom Blundell works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Touch on the shorter side, on off. Henry Nicholls fends it from his crease.
Flatter and quicker on off. Henry Nicholls pushes it to mid off for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle. Henry Nicholls works it to mid on for a single.
Tossed up on mddle. Tom Blundell drives it to long on for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Henry Nicholls presses forward to defend and gets a thick outside edge that goes past the diving slip fielder for a couple.
Goes fuller and on off. Henry Nicholls drives it to long off for a single.
Tossed up on leg. Tom Blundell turns it around the croner for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Excellent review by Babar Azam! Agha Salman picks up his third wicket and that means that New Zealand have lost half of their side now. This is short and quicker outside off. Henry Nicholls tries to cut it but seems to have missed it. However, Babar Azam seem to have heard something and after a brief discussion, he takes the DRS. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows a spike as the ball passes the bat and the decision of not out is overturned. Brilliant from the Pakistani skipper as Sarfaraz Ahmed, the wicketkeeper did not even appeal.
Howout: c Sarfaraz Ahmed b Agha Salman

Commentary: On leg, this is flicked through square leg for one.
Tossed up on off. Michael Bracewell drives it to mid off.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust as New Zealand lose their sixth now. Michael Bracewell walks back for a duck. Ahmed pitches it on off and turns into Michael Bracewell. He tries to defend it but misses it altogether and gets hit on the pads. Abrar Ahmed makes a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger immediately. Michael Bracewell knows he is gone and does not even bother to take the DRS. Pakistan are right on top now.
Howout: lbw b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Tossed up and on leg. Sodhi clips it to mid-wicket this time.
Flatter and quicker on middle. Sodhi fends it towards the leg side.
Lovely in-drifter on middle. Sodhi is equal to the task as he blocks it out solidly.
It is tossed up, on middle. Tom Blundell presses forward and blocks it to the leg side off the inner half.
Tom Blundell comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
It is full and on off. Tom Blundell sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Full, straying on the pads. Ish Sodhi flicks it to square leg for a single.
Loops it up, outside off. Tom Blundell blocks it off his front foot.
Tom Blundell clips it off his pads towards fine leg for an easy single.

Back of a length, on off. Tom Blundell goes back and knocks it down to wide of long on. Naseem Shah gives it a chase, dives across and is able to stop the ball. Although, he gets a cramp in the process and is down on the field. He desperately reaches the ball and throws it back. Two runs are taken. He cools down his muscles and is back on his feet.
On off, blocked on the front foot.
It is full, on middle and leg. Tom Blundell defends it out watchfully.
Pushed through quicker, on leg. Tom Blundell dabs it down.
On a length, outside off. this one climbs on the batter. Tom Blundell hangs back and fends it out.
It is full, on middle and leg. Tom Blundell nudges it to the leg side.
Tossed up, on off. Ish Sodhi blocks it back to the bowler.
Outside off, full. Sodhi taps it to the off side.

BYE! The SECOND NEW BALL has been taken by Pakistan now. Gets some purchase straight away. This lands on off and turns away down leg. Ish Sodhi leaves it alone, while the keeper parries it behind square leg. One bye taken.
Outside off, Blundell uses his feet and blocks it out.
A single now as this is punched to cover-point.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Ish Sodhi blocks it out solidly off his front foot.
Good length, outside off. Tom Blundell looks to chase it but misses.
On off, defended out.
A length ball, around off. Tom Blundell punches it through covers for a single.
Quite short, wide of off, tapped to covers.
A slower length ball, sliding down leg. Sodhi tucks it to the leg side for a single.
It is full, angling across the right-hander. Tom Blundell drives it to mid off but straight to the fielder.
Ali starts with a full one, outside off. Sodhi pushes it to cover.
Ish Sodhi taps this good-length delivery into the off side.
Much fuller, wide of off. Sodhi reaches out and helps it to the man at point.
Good length, in the channel. Ish Sodhi shuffles and blocks it out watchfully.

FOUR! EDGED BUT SAFE! Ali serves it full and outside off. Ish Sodhi only finds a thick outside edge as he tries to drive it through the off side. The ball though flies past the man at gully and races away to the fence.
Length and on off, defended out watchfully by Sodhi. Only 5 overs are remaining now. Will Pakistan be able to get a couple more wickets before the Stumps on Day 1?
NO BALL! Mir Hamza has overstepped here! Lands it on a good length and it is outside off. Tom Blundell leaves it alone.
Serves it on a length angles it on middle. Tom Blundell blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on middle. Tom Blundell rides the bounce and works it towards the leg side.

A fullish delivery on off angled from 'round the wicket. Tom Blundell fends it to mid off and sets off for a single. The fielder at mid off fires a direct hit at the batter's end but Sodhi is safe as the replays confirm it.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Sodhi manages to just about clip it to backward square leg for a single.
NO BALL! Another no ball from Mir Hamza! Overstepping again as he lands it on a length, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it out.
Angles a length delivery on off. Blundell blocks it out solidly.
Serves it on a length again and around off. Blundell fends it towards the off side without much fuss.
Back of a length, on off. Sodhi stands tall and blocks it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Shorish and outside off. Sodhi cuts it and cuts it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Lands it on a length, on off. Sodhi defends it from his crease towards the off side.
Bangs it short and around off. Sodhi sways away from the line of the ball.
On a length and around off. Sodhi fends it towards the off side this time.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Sodhi blocks it from his crease back to the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely timed! Shortish and on middle. Blundell goes back and punches it wide of mid on for a boundary.
Pushes it quicker and touch shorter on off. Blundell blocks it out.
Tossed up and on middle. Tom Blundell with a solid front foot defence.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Blundell fends it back to bowler with ease.
Floated up nicely and it is outside of this time. Tom Blundell lets it go.
On middle and quicker. Tom Blundell works it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Tom Blundell fends it off the back foot.
On a length, on off. Blundell gets well forward to defend this now.
Just short of good length and around off. Blundell defends it towards the off side with ease.
Goes fuller and on off. Blundell drives it to mid off fielder.
FOUR! Sublime timing from Tom Blundell! Overpitched delivery, outside off. Blundell leans forward and creams it through covers for a beautiful looking boundary.
On a length, on off. Blundell pushes it to the mid off fielder this time.
Tossed up and on middle. Sodhi fends it towards the leg side.
Loopy and slower through the air, on middle. Sodhi with a front foot defence.
Pushes it quicker and on off. Ish Sodhi defends it again off the front foot.
Touch shorter and around off. Sodhi fends it towards the off side.
Bowls it quicker and flatter on off. Sodhi goes back and blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on off to end the day! Sodhi takes his front foot forward and blocks it out solidly. That's Stumps on Day 1!
Starts off with a length delivery on middle. Tom Blundell is right behind it to block it.
A fullish delivery on off at 130.7 kph. Blundell drives it to the cover fielder this time.
Serves it on a length, on middle. Blundell fends it back to the bowler.
Lands on a length again on middle. Blundell with a solid block again.
On a length, on off at 129.3 kph. Blundell takes his front foot forward and defends it out towards the off side.
A maiden to start the proceedings on Day 2! Keeps it on a good length, on off. Blundell is happy to block it right under his eyes.
Angles a length delivery on leg. Sodhi tries to clip it but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards leg side.
A fullish delivery on middle. Sodhi fends it off the inside half of his blade.
Lands it on a good length, on off. Sodhi defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! BOWLED! Naseem Shah strikes in his fourth delivery of the day and New Zealand now lose their seventh. This is a perfect delivery, lands it on a good length, on off and it seams away just a bit to beat the outside edge of Sodhi's blade as he tries to defend it. The ball hits the top of the off stump and Naseem Shah who was the pick of the bowlers on Day 1 has started Day 2 in a fine fashion here. Third wicket for the young man!
Howout: b Naseem Shah

Commentary: On a length, on middle. Southee fends it towards the leg side.
Lands it on a good length again, on off. Tim Southee blocks it from his crease. A wicket-maiden from Shah to follow a maiden from Mir Hamza.
Lands it on a length, on off. Blundell fends it back to the bowler. Good start from the Pakistani bowlers, they are making batters play almost every ball here.
Back of a length, on off. He angles it from 'round the wicket and Tom Blundell rides the bounce nicely to block it.
Serves a length delivery on middle. Blundell works it towards mid-wicket with the angle.
Just short of good length, on off. Tom Blundell blocks it from his crease.
Angles a length delivery on off at 128.1 kph. Blundell is solid in his block again.
Still no run for New Zealand this morning! Back of a length, on off. Blundell fends it nicely towards the off side.
Serves it on a length, on middle. Southee blocks it to the mid on region.

Appeal for LBW from the bowler but the umpire and his teammates are not interested! Back of a length, on off and it nips back in. Southee tries to clip it away but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Back of a length, on leg. Southee clips it to fine leg for a single.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Blundell drives it firmly to the cover fielder.
Back of a length and around off. Blundell fends it towards the off side and looks for a single but is sent back by Southee.
Touch fuller and on off. Blundell drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Back of a length and angles it on leg. Blundell works it to fine leg for a single.

Was there an edge? Yes, Sarfaraz Ahmed says that he heard the sound. Back of a length and outside off. Southee goes for a drive but gets an outside edge that goes off the bounce to the keeper, Sarfaraz Ahmed.

FOUR! In the gap and first boundary of the day! Back of a length and around off. Southee stays deep in his crease and pushes at it. The ball goes off the thick outside edge of his blade through the gully region for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Southee blocks it out.
On a length and angles it on off. Southee manages to keep it out safely again.
Beaten! On a good length and outside off. Southee pokes at it tentatively and gets beaten as the ball straightens after pitching.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Blundell works it to the mid-wicket fielder.
A fullish delivery, on off. Blundell with a solid block off the front foot.
Back of a length, on off. Blundell defends it back to the bowler.
Serves it on a length, on off. Blundell blocks it again without much fuss.
FOUR! Lovely shot! A fullish delivery and outside off. Blundell leans forward and caresses it through covers for a beautiful boundary. He is looking at ease here.
Shah corrects his length and lands it on a good length, on off. Blundell defends it back to the bowler.
On the shorter side and angling into leg. Southee pulls it towards deep backward square leg where Shah slides to his left and keeps it to just a single.
Short of good length and around off. Blundell fends it towards the off side.
Touch shorter and around off. Blundell pushes it gently towards the off side and takes a single.
Back of a length, on off. Southee pushes it towards covers nicely.
Back of a length, on off at 125.5 kph. Southee rides the bounce and punches it to mid off.
Back of a length and bit of width provided as well. Southee chops it to deep point for a single.
Short and outside off. Southee pushes it to point and the batters steal a quick single.
Serves it on a full length, on middle. Blundell drives it to the mid on fielder.
Lands a beautiful length delivery on off. Blundell fends it off the front foot.
Back of a length and around off. Blundell chops it towards the point fielder.
On a length, around off. Blundell pushes it to covers for a single.
Serves a fullish delivery on middle. Southee drives it to the mid off fielder.
Back of a length, around off angling from 'round the wicket. Blundell defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Shortish and around off. Blundell chops it towards backward point.
Oh, beaten! Back of a length and it is outside off. Blundell tries to guide it towards the gully region but gets beaten.
Angles a length delivery on middle and leg this time. Blundell clips it to fine leg for a single.
Goes fuller and around off. Southee drives but finds the fielder at mid off.
A slower delivery this time. On a length and outside off. Southee waits for it and then pushes it to cover-point for a single.
Lands it on a length, on off. Southee walks down the pitch and pushes it to mid on.
On a length, on off. Southee works it to mid on again.
Back of a length, on off. Southee rides the bounce and blocks it out.
Bit of reverse there! A full delivery and it shapes into the batter. Southee tries to clip it towards the leg side but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Back of a length and outside off. Southee punches it to the cover-point region where Imam-ul-Haq dives to his right and saves a certain boundary.
Back of a length and around off. Southee punches it to the cover fielder.
FOUR! Powerful shot. It is short, wide of off. Tom Blundell rocks back and punches it through covers for four.
On off, blocked on the front foot.
This is full angled into the pads, Tom Blundell defends it with full face.
A single now as this is pushed to covers.
Loops it up, on off, defended out.
It is tossed up, around off. Tim Southee remains solid in his defense.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Blundell square drives it to deep point for a single.

Good bouncer! Ali bangs it short and on middle. Southee tries to pull it but is early in his shot and ends up missing it to get hit on the helmet. The physio comes out now for the mandatory concussion test and all seems fine as Southee is ready to resume.
Back of a length, on off. Southee works it towards mid-wicket nicely.
Back of a length and around off. Southee stays still in his crease and blocks it out.
Tries out the batter with a bouncer again! Bowls it short and angles it on middle and leg. Tim Southee ducks under it.

Ali with another good delivery that lands just short of good length. It pitches around off and nips back in as Southee misses it while trying to block. He gets hit on the pads and Ali makes a lound appeal and the umpire raises his finger. However, Southee reviews and the UltraEdge shows no bat here but the Ball Tracking shows that the ball is going over the stumps. So, Southee survives.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Blundell blocks it out.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up on middle. Blundell skips down the track and lifts it over mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up and on off. Blundell with a solid front foot defence.
FIFTY for Tom Blundell! This has been anothe solid knock from the keeper-batter. He continues to grow in stature, This is a fuller delivery on middle. Blundell knocks it to long on for a single.
Slower through the air and on off. Southee blocks it off the front foot.
Pushes it quicker and on off. Southee fends it again nicely.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Blundell defends it towards the leg side.
Serves it on a length and on off. Blundell fends it from his crease.
Bangs it short and around off. Blundell tries to pull it but misses and the ball goes back to the keeper.
Back of a length and around off. Blundell punches it to deep point for a single.
WIDE! Bowls it short again and this tme is around leg. Bit high too and Southee ducks under it. Wide called!
Bangs it short again, around off. Southee is happy to duck under it.
Back of a length and around off. Southee punches it to the mid on fielder.

OUT! TIMBER! Well, Abrar Ahmed strikes right after the drinks break. Pakistan will be feeling great now. It is a carrom ball, on middle and leg, that stays very low off the deck. Tom Blundell rocks back but is unable to push it away to safety. The ball sneaks under his blade to shatter the stumps.
Howout: b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Looped up, around off, blocked out.
Full and on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Short and on off. Henry goes back and offers full face.
Tossed up, outside off. Henry looks to chase it but misses.
FOUR! This is much better from Henry. It is full and on off. Matt Henry gets low and slogs it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
An inswinger, full and on the pads, Tim Southee flicks it behind square on the leg side for one.
Full and attacking the stumps. Henry dabs it back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out.
It is overpitched on off. Henry eases it to mid off.
A sharp bouncer, on the body. Henry sways away from the line of the delivery.
Just a single off the over then! Fraction short, in the channel. Henry hits it through the line to the off side.

OUT! STUMPED! Abrar Ahmed is on a roll this morning. He gets his third wicket of the innings. It is tossed up, outside off. Tim Southee dances down the track and looks to go downtown but gets beaten by the away turn this time. Sarfaraz Ahmed is quick to gather the ball and clip the bails in a flash. He thinks he has got his man here. The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays show that Tim Southee had his back leg in the air.
Howout: st Sarfaraz Ahmed b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Fuller and outside off. Patel tries to sweep it away but misses.
Three dots in a row now. It is full and on off. Patel presses forward and blocks it out.
It is tossed up, wide of off. Turning in with some extra bounce.Patel gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller, on off, defended out watchfully. A wicket-taking over by Ahmed comes to an end.
This is full, tailing into the batter from outside off. Matt Henry gives room and works it down the ground.
Ali goes full, on leg. This one stays very low off the deck. Henry tucks it off his pads.
Inswinging full, on middle and leg. Henry whips it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Incredible shot. It is a short ball, outside off. Matt Henry stays back and frees his arms this time. He slashes it over covers for a cracking boundary.

FOUR! Up and over! Matt Henry is not sitting back here. He gets another boundary here. A genuine half-volley, on off. Matt Henry stands tall and lofts it well over the man at mid off. The ball races away.
SIX! This is huge! Matt Henry is putting up a solid show. It is a short ball, on off. Matt Henry stands tall and pulls it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
On off, blocked.
Full, sliding down leg. Ajaz Patel sweeps it past short leg.
Ajaz Patel goes for the sweep once again but takes a blow on his pads.
It is tossed up, around off. It leaves the left-handed batter with a sharp turn. Patel gets beaten.
On off, Patel remains solid in his defense.
This is full and on off. Patel keeps his eyes on the ball and smothers it away.
Fuller, attacking the stumps. Henry knocks it into covers.
Goes full, outside off. It shapes away a touch. Henry taps it through point for a couple of runs.
FOUR! What a shot! It is overpitched, on off. Matt Henry goes back and smashes it through covers. It comes off the middle and races away to the fence.
A short ball, on off. Henry pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
It is full, outside off, coming in with the angle. Patel eases it back to the bowler.
Full again, attacking the off pole. Patel remains solid in his defense.
Ahmed goes full, on middle and leg. Henry slogs it to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Short, just outside off, punched to covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Patel paddles it behind square on the leg side for one.
Floats it up, full and on off. Matt Henry lofts it over mid off for a single.
Another single now as this is worked into the off side.
Looped up, around leg. Henry gets clipped on his pads. Ahmed makes a stifled appeal but the umpire stays unmoved. Pakistan are forced to work really hard for this final wicket.
FOUR BYES! It is a short ball, sliding down leg. Ajaz Patel stays back and looks to pull it away. He misses and so does the keeper, as the ball flies past his diving effort and races away.
A low full toss, on middle. Patel nudges it to the leg side.
On a length, around off. Patel punches it to covers.
Back of a length, outside off. Ajaz Patel swivels and pulls it to mid-wicket for one.

Good length, going down leg. Matt Henry tries to flick it but misses to take a blow on his pads. Naseem Shah makes an appeal for lbw but it is turned down. Babar Azam gives it a thought and takes the review. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking confirms that the ball is missing the wicket. Pakistan lose a review here.
Overpitched on off. Henry strokes it to extra cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Ajaz Patel tries to defend but does so inside the line.
Outside off, left alone.
It is full and on off, coming in with the arm. Defended.
Floats it up, around middle. Patel looks to sweep it away but takes a blow high on his pads.
It is looped up, going down leg. Patel works it out off his pads.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is flighted and on off. Ajaz Patel gets low and slogs it towards deep mid-wicket. They get four runs.

SIX! Matt Henry races into his 30s. This stand moves to 40 as well in no time. It is a short ball, on off. Matt Henry stands tall and dispatches it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. Looks like the ball is lost as well.
A low full toss, on off, pushed to mid off.
Fraction short, on off. Henry blocks it out.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Matt Henry clips it to mid-wicket. They take one.
Goes full this time, on middle and leg. Patel pushes it to cover.
OUCH! Back of a length, on the body. Ajaz Patel swivels on his back foot and looks to pull it away but he ends up taking a blow on his ribs.
Short, outside off. Cut away to covers.
This is pushed through quicker, on off. Henry squares up a bit but blocks it out.
FOUR! Swept away! It is tossed up, full and outside off. Matt Henry gets low and slogs it in the gap at deep mid-wicket to find a boundary.
On off, knocked into covers for a single.
Another single now as Patel works it to long on.
Tossed up, on off. Henry lofts it towards long on. There is a misfield there which allows the batters to take a couple. Henry now gets into his 40s.
It is a short ball, on off. Patel pulls it to deep square leg for a single. The stand moves to 50 runs now. Pakistan will be extremely gutted with the way this is turning out to be.
Short again, on the bodyline from 'round the wicket. Henry pulls it to deep square leg. It lands safely though. They take one.
Back of a length, on off. Patel pulls it to deep mid-wicket for two runs.
Short again, down leg. Patel pulls it along the ground to square leg.
Back of a length, again. Patel pulls it past short leg.
Guess what, it is short yet again. Patel heaves it across the line but only to find the fielder at square leg.
On off, defended out.

There is some luck on Henry's side here. It is full and on off. Henry dances down the track and looks to go downtown. The ball takes a thick inside edge, scoots past the leg pole and goes to fine leg. Two taken.
This is turning into the pads with some extra bounce. Henry misses his flick and takes a blow.
Short and on off. Henry punches it to cover for one.

FOUR! Off the edge. It is tossed up, around off. Patel opens the face and guides it through the slip cordon off the outside edge. The ball races away to the third man fence as Hamza escorts it to the fence rather than chasing it down.
This is swept to square leg for one.
Full, tailing into the batter. Patel tucks it to the leg side.
This is full again, around off, it nips back in. Patel tries to whip it away but misses.
It is fuller, going down leg. Patel takes a blow on his pads. Hamza makes an appeal but the umpire shows no interest.
Once again, sliding down leg, on a fuller length. Patel misses his tuck. He gets pinged on his pads.
Length and on off, driven down the ground.
FOUR! Top shot! It is a full-length ball, on off. Ajaz Patel strokes it through the gap at covers for a fine boundary.
Tossed up on middle. Henry skips down the track and tries to heave it towards the leg side but misses. The ball goes off his pads towards the off side. A leg bye is taken.
Shortish and on off. Patel punches it to covers for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short and wide outside off. Henry cuts it through point for a boundary.
Fifty for Matt Henry! What a knock this has been, terrific stuff! Touch short and outside off. Henry cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up and on middle. Patel pushes it to mid on for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Henry blocks it off the front foot.
Lands it on a length, on middle. Patel fends it towards the mid on fielder.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Patel flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Henry pushes it to deep cover for a single.
Bowls it short and on middle. Patel pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
On a length and around off. Henry pushes it left of mid off for a single.
A full toss on off. Patel drives it to mid on for a single.
Tossed up, on off, defended to the left of the bowler.
Just short of full length. It flies off the deck. Patel gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and on off. Punched to point.
Back of a length, wide of off. Patel gets it to point off the outside edge.
Pushed through quicker, on off, blocked out.
Ajaz Patel tries to flick this full delivery on leg but misses. The ball lobs to the off side off his boots.
Length ball, angled in from outside off. Matt Henry offers a straight bat.

In the air...Safe! It is full and outside off. Matt Henry throws the kitchen sink at it. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards third man. Abdullah Shafique there runs in from the deep but realises it late that he won't get there in time. He takes a pause in his charge. Tha ball lands in front of him and they take a single.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Back of a length, on off. Ajaz Patel rides the bounce and pulls it towards cow corner for a couple.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Patel presses forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
This is full, sliding down leg. Patel takes a blow on his pads as misses to work it around the corner.
Slower through the air, full and outside off. Matt Henry defends it on his front foot.
Pushed through quicker, on leg. Henry tries to block it away but takes a blow on his pads.
On off, defended to covers.
Matt Henry gets on his front foot to block this delivery but takes a blow high on his pads.
Around leg. Henry clips it behind square on the leg side.
Full and on off, driven into covers for one. The only run that comes off this over.
Short and on off. Henry goes back and blocks it out.
Much fuller, on off. Henry goes for the sweep but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On off, dabbed down by Henry.
Tosses it up, around off. Henry blocks it to the off side.
Henry now rotates the strike as he flicks it to square leg off his pads.

A googly, outside off. Patel opens the face late and steers it down to third man. The batters take a couple with ease. We should get one more over before the Lunch break here. The stand for the final wicket moves to 85 runs.
Flatter and short, outside off. Henry punches it to sweeper cover for one.
It is outside off, left alone.
Loops it up, wide of off. Turning away a touch. Patel has no shot to offer.
Fraction short, outside off, turning away. Ajaz Patel looks to chase it but misses.
It is full and on off. Patel gets under it and lodts it over covers. The batters take a couple of runs.
A short ball, wide outside off. Ajaz Patel reaches out and cuts it to point. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Starts off with a tossed up delivery on off. Henry fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it fuller and on off again. Henry sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
On off and slower through the air. Patel defends it calmly off the front foot.
Fires it around leg and Patel leaves it alone. The ball goes off his pads towards leg slip.
FOUR! Oh, quality shot! Tossed up on off. Patel leans forward and tonks it down the ground for a boundary.
Slower through the air, on off. Patel defends it with soft hands towards the leg side.
Tossed up delivery turning into off. Henry punches it to covers.
Flighted delivery on middle. Henry skips down the track and tries to work it towards the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Fullish delivery on off. Henry pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle. Henry skips down the track and knocks it to long on for a single.
Touch shorter and on off. Patel punches it to the cover fielder.
A slider on middle and leg. Patel tries to defend it off the front foot but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal follows but the umpire is not interested.
Tossed up on off. Henry fends it off the front foot.
Slower and around off. Henry pushes it to covers.
Bowls it flatter and quicker on middle. Henry blocks it out.
Quicker and fuller on middle. Henry pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Henry sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Patel fends it off the front foot with soft hands.
FOUR! Tossed up, on off. Henry drills it straight down the ground. Imam-ul-Haq makes a diving effort at long on but fails to stop it.
Flighted delivery on off. Henry shimmies down the track and gets hit on the pads as he tries to defend.
Bowls it fuller and quicker on middle. Henry drives it back to the bowler.
Fires it quicker and flatter on middle. Henry punches it back to the bowler.
On off and turning into the batter. Henry is quick to defend it off the back foot.
FOUR! 100 partnership comes up! What a performance this has been from Henry and Ajaz Patel! Tossed up on middle. Henry shimmies down the track and slams it down the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off. Patel dabs it towards the off side.
On the shorter side and angling into off. Patel tries to push it but gets an inside edge just past stumps.
Short of good length and on off. Patel pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and around off again. Patel very calmly pushes it to the point fielder.
Goes fuller and on off. Patel drives it to back to the bowler with more solidity.
Serves it fuller again and angles it on middle. Patel drives it off the inside half of his blade to mid on.
This is full and on leg. Henry pats it back to Ahmed.
Loops it up, on middle. Henry gets on his front foot to block it away.
On off, blocked.
