Full, attacking the stumps. Henry drives it into covers.
Matt Henry flicks this length ball off his pads for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! There it is... Abrar Ahmed gets the final wicket here and the Kiwis get all out for 449 runs. It is a googly, around off. Ajaz Patel does not pick up the delivery and goes for the slog-sweep. All he manages to get is a top-edge. The ball flies off the top edge and goes behind the keeper. Agha Salman from slips moves to his right, settles under it and takes a dolly.
Howout: c Agha Salman b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: FOUR! Deft touch! Runs for Pakistan and Abdullah Shafique straight away. It is a good-length ball that lands on off and shapes away a bit. Abdullah Shafique plays it with soft hands and gets in between gully and the slip cordon off the outer half. The ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
It is a length ball, on top of off, shaping in a bit. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and blocks it into the deck.
This is full, on leg stump. Abdullah Shafique squares up and blocks it towards mid on.
Southee goes full again, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique tries to flick it away but gets it to mid on off the outer half.
A length ball, sliding down leg. Abdullah Shafique tucks it square to the leg side.

Tim Southee makes a solid comeback after going for a boundary off the very first delivery. The only runs that came in this over. It is a length ball, on middle. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out watchfully.
Henry starts with a length ball, angling across the left-hander. Imam-ul-Haq shoulders his arms at it.
Another sighter for Imam-ul-Haq, as even this is outside off, angling away. Imam-ul-Haq is hesistant to play away from his body so early on.
This is on a good length, in the channel. Imam-ul-Haq gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Imam-ul-Haq stays on his back foot and cuts this good-length ball late towards backward point. The fielder there dives to his right to stop the ball.
This is much fuller, although wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone for the keeper.
This is much closer to the batter but Imam-ul-Haq reads it well to make a solid leave. Matt Henry starts his spell with a maiden over.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Abdullah Shafique defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Good length, wide of off. Abdullah Shafique lets it be.
It is a length ball, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off his front foot.
Length, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it into covers off his front foot.
It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Abdullah Shafique tucks it to mid-wicket.
LEG BYE! A full-length ball, sliding down leg. Abdullah Shafique gets rapped on his pads as he fails to flick it away. They collect a leg bye.
Length, on middle and leg, blocked watchfully.
This is much fuller, outside off. Abdullah Shafique gets on his front foor and tries to block it out. The ball goes to deep square leg off the inside edge. The batters take two.
Henry goes short, on top of off. Abdullah Shafique rocks back and defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Nicely played. Abdullah Shafique is getting into his rhythm here. It is a good-length ball, around off. Abdullah Shafique goes back and punches it through the gap at cover regio for four runs. His second boundary of the innings.
Abdullah Shafique flicks this full delivery to deep square leg and crosses.
A dot to end the over! Henry serves it full, around off, leaving the left-hander. Imam-ul-Haq shuffles and shoulders his arms at it.
A length ball, outside off, nips in a touch. Abdullah Shafique blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, left alone.
This is full, angled into the pads. Abdullah Shafique presses forward and defends it out solidly.
Four dots now! On a length, wide of off. Abdullah Shafique shoulders his arms at it.
FOUR! Put away with ease. Southee spills it on a fuller length, down leg. Abdullah Shafique flicks it to deep square leg and finds the boundary. The home crowd is loving the start their side has got.

FOUR! Exceptional boundary. A loud cheer escorts the ball into the ropes once again. Tim Southee goes full this time, on off. Abdullah Shafique creams it down the ground off the front foot. It races away past mid off and into the fence.
A length ball, angling across the left-hander. Left alone.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Imam-ul-Haq. He gets off the mark in fine fashion. It is a short ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes back and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
A short ball, on off. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to deep square leg but does not middle it. He manages to keep it away from the man in the deep. They take a single.
A short ball, on leg stump. Abdullah Shafique bends his knees and sways away from the line just like a move in the matrix movie.
Length, on off, defended out watchfully.
Good length, on top of off. Abdullah Shafique deals with it by playing a solid defensive shot.
Tossed up, on off, blocked to the left of the bowler off the front foot.
Touch fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq remains solid in his defense.
It is full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq leans in and drives it to the right of mid off. They cross for a quick single.
Outside off, blocked into covers off the front foot.
This one come in with the arm, full and on leg as Patel comes 'round the wicket. Abdullah Shafique gets it to point off the outer half.
Full and on off, defended out on the front foot. A tidy start by Patel with the ball. He shined with the bat eariler. Will he be able to do something similar with the ball in hand?
Henry dishes a full-length ball, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq dabs it towards cover.
A single now as this good-length ball is pulled behind square on the leg side by Imam-ul-Haq.
Fuller, outside off. Abdullah Shafique blocks it off his front foot.
Much fuller, outside off, this one holds its line. Abdullah Shafique shoulders his arms at it.

OUT! CAUGHT! The pair for the last wicket stand for the Kiwis have an instant impact in the field as well as they both combine for the first wicket. Matt Henry strikes early on and the Kiwis would surely be delighted to see the back of Abdullah Shafique who looked to be in good touch. It is a short ball, on off. Abdullah Shafique swivels and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. He could not keep his shot under control and Ajaz Patel takes a sharp catch in the deep to spread silence across the stadium.
Howout: c Ajaz Patel b Matt Henry

Commentary: Length and on off, defended out solidly. A successful over by Henry comes to an end.
FOUR! Imam-ul-Haq now taking the charge here. Imam-ul-Haq uses his feet and turns it into a full toss. He whips is past mid-wicket and finds a boundary.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq comes down the track and blocks it into covers.
Imam-ul-Haq uses his feet once again and strokes it to long off.
Loops it up, outside off. blocked out.
This is touch fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq dances down the track and defends it to mid off.
Fraction short, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq cuts it to sweeper cover. There is protection in the deep. Two taken.

FOUR! Timed it to perfection. Shan Masood gets off the mark with a good-looking boundary. This should certainly help his confidence. It is a length ball, around off. Shan Masood stands tall and knocks it down the park, along the ground for four runs.

LEG BYE! A length ball, on leg stump. This one climbs on the batter. Shan Masood fails to clip it away. It goes to square leg off his thigh pads. The batters collect a leg bye as the umpire shows no interest to Henry's appeal.
Back of a length, around middle. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Shan Masood gets an under-edge on this short delivery as he fails to get a good connection on his pull shot.
A short ball, going down leg. Shan Masood stays back and helps it to deep square leg. They take two before the fielder cuts it out.
Short again and pulled again through square leg. The batters call for two and get it safely.
Full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq slogs it to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Shan Masood has his eye-in here. It is full and on off. Shan Masood dances down the track and drills it down to long off for four runs.
On off, blocked out.
FOUR! Wonderful stroke! Shan Masood gets his second boundary of the over. It is tossed up, full and outside off. Shan Masood uses his feet and creams it through the gap at covers for four runs.
FOUR! Shan Masood is on a roll here. It is looped up, full and on middle. Shan Masood dances down the track and lofts it over mid on. One bounce and into the ropes.

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh dear, Shan Masood tries to put this poor delivery away for a boundary but holes out instead. He should've left this one, given the runs he had racked up in the over already. Very poor shot selection by Masood. This is a short ball, outside off and a bit quicker. Shan Masood rocks back and tries to cut it away. Although, he hits it straight down the throat of Devon Conway at backward point who makes no mistake. Ajaz Patel joins his partner in crime, Matt Henry in the wicket's column.
Howout: c Devon Conway b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Henry bends his back hard, and serves a short ball, around off. Imam-ul-Haq hops and blocks it into the deck.
Just short! Back of a length, on the body. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to the left of short fine leg. Daryl Mitchell dives to that side but is unable to gather the ball.
On off, blocked.
This is spilled down leg. Imam-ul-Haq lets it be.
Imam-ul-Haq pulls this short ball, straight to Kane Williamson who makes a half-stop. The batters take a single.
A dot to end the over! A good-length ball, wide of off. Azam punches it to point off his back foot.
Fires a quicker delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq works it to mid-wicket.
Touch shorter and on off. Imam-ul-Haq goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Bowls it flatter and on off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it solidly again.
Turning into middle and quicker too. Imam-ul-Haq works it to the square leg fielder.
Patel bowls it outside off and keeps it short of full length as Imam-ul-Haq tucks it towards the leg side.
Serves it fuller and on off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward and defends it.
Lands it on a length, on off at 135.7 kph. Azam defends it right under his eyes.
A fullish delivery and close to the off pole again. Azam with a solid block again.
Back of a length and on off. Azam fends it back to the bowler.
A fullish delivery and around off at 134.4 kph. Azam presses forward to defend it nicely yet again.
Lands it on a good length and around off. The ball seams away a bit after pitching and beats the outside edge of Azam's blade as he tries to defend it.
A fullish delivery on off and it comes into Babar a bit. He covers the line of the ball and defends it towards the leg side.
Quite short, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq punches it through cover-point for a single.
Tossed up, around off. Azam blocks it out watchfully.
On off, defended out.
FOUR! Trademark Babar Azam. Michael Bracewell drags his length back, outside off. Babar Azam punches it through the line off his backfoot. It races away through covers for four runs.
Full and on off, blocked to silly point.
Floats it up, around Azam presses forward and defends it to silly point once again. It's Tea on Day 2!
Shortish and on off. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to widish mid on.
Bowls it quicker and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes back and blocks it out.
Serves it fuller and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq takes a big stride forward and defends it.
Touch shorter and quicker on off. Imam-ul-Haq goes deep in his crease and works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Nice in-drifter on off. Azam defends it towards the leg side.
Serves it fuller and on middle. Azam gets well forward and blocks it.
Tosses it up, on off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it off the front foot.
Bowls almost a yorker-length delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out.
Touch shorter on off. Imam-ul-Haq goes right behind it to block it.
Slower through the air, on off. Imam-ul-Haq fends it off the front foot.
Angles it into middle and quicker as Imam-ul-Haq fends it off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
Tosses it up and on off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it to the cover fielder.
Angles it on middle and flatter. Babar Azam defends it solidly off the front foot.
Goes fuller and on off. Azam drives it to the mid off fielder.
SIX! Great use of the feet! Tossed up on off. Azam skips down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and tonks it over long on for a maximum.
Slower through the air, on off. Azam fends it off the front foot.
Goes fuller and around off. Azam drives it the cover fielder.
Lovely delivery! Bit of more flight, on off and with some good drift as well as Azam gets well forward and blocks it out.
Bowls it quicker and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Imam-ul-Haq shimmies down the track and drives it to long off for a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Touch shorter and outside off. Azam goes deep in his crease and just cuts it late as the ball runs away towards the backward point fence.
Tossed up on off. Azam drives it to the cover fielder.
Tossed up nicely on off. Azam blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off. Enticing the batter to go for a big shot but Azam is happy to block it.
Well played! Touch shorter and around off. Imam-ul-Haq late-cuts it towards the third man region for a couple.
Angles it on middle and quicker. Azam clips it to square leg.
Loopy delivery and on middle. Azam skips down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Flatter and quicker on off. Azam blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on off. Azam fends it off the front foot nicely.
Touch short of full length, on off. Babar is well forward again and pushes it gently towards the off side.
Tossed up nicely on off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward to defend it.
Touch short of full length, on off. Imam-ul-Haq tries to defend again off the front foot but gets an outside edge towards the gully region and a single is taken.
Touch shorter and turning into middle. Azam works it to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up and on middle. Azam fends it off the front foot.
Bowls it outside off and it turns a bit but Azam plays it comfortably towards the off side.
Bowls it shorter and outside off. Azam waits for it and late-cuts it through the gully region for a couple.
Serves it on a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Lands it on a length and outside off again. Imam-ul-Haq lets it go watchfully.
FOUR! Good shot! Pure timing, an overpitched delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq shows the full face of his blade as he drives it straight past the bowler for a boundary.
On a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
Angles a length delivery on off and Imam-ul-Haq blocks it from his crease.
Serves a fullish delivery on off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it back to the bowler.
Short and on off. Azam goes back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it right of mid off for an easy single.
Slower through the air and touch short on off. Azam gets a big stride foward and blocks it out.
On the shorter side and on middle. Azam clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Fires it quicker and flatter on middle. Imam-ul-Haq works it to backward square leg.
Flighted one and on off. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward to defend it.
On a length, on off. Azam with a front foot defence.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shortish delivery and outside off. Bit close to cut but Babar Azam manages to still cut it through the backward point region for a boundary.
A full delivery and outside off. Babar Azam drives it to the short cover fielder.
Serves it full and on middle. Azam flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Lands it on a length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq lets it go.
FOUR! Now this is a shot of a man who is high in confidence! A fullish delivery this, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leans foward and plays a beautiful cover drive as the ball races away towards the fence.
Touch shorter and around off. Azam goes back and pushes it to cover-point for a single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Massive, massive miscommunication between the batters and Babar Azam pays the price! This is a flatter delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq goes back and works it towards the deep mid-wicket region. The batters take the first run quickly. Azam takes the second quickly as well while Imam-ul-Haq is tad slow in the second run. He is ball watching and as Azam runs for the third, Imam-ul-Haq sends his partner back way too late as he is in no positon to take that third run. The throw comes in from Henry Nicholls at the bowler's end and Babar Azam is nowhere in the picture as Michael Bracewell whips the bails off. Babar Azam is not a happy man and rightly so, he wass looking so good out there. New Zealand have got a bonus wicket!
Howout: run out (Henry Nicholls / Michael Bracewell)

Commentary: A flatter delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq works it to the leg side.
Fuller and on middle. Blocked nicely by Imam-ul-Haq.
Tossed up and on off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it off the front foot here.
Quicker and fuller on middle. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to mid on.
On a length and around off. Saud Shakeel fends it towards the off side.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Saud Shakeel lets it go.
Bowls it full and outside off again and Saud Shakeel is happy to let it go.
On a length and around off. Saud Shakeel fends it off the outside half of his blade towards the off side.
Beaten! Angles a length delivery, around off. Saud Shakeel pushes forward to defend but the ball straightens and beats the outside edge of his blade.
On a length and way outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves it alone.
Touch shorter and on off. Imam-ul-Haq works it to mid-wicket.
Touch quicker and flatter on leg. Imam-ul-Haq clips it to square leg for a single.
Slower through the air, on off. Saud Shakeel fends it nicely off the front foot.
Flighted delivery and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it out.
Bit quicker and fuller on off. Saud Shakeel defends it off the outside half of his blade.
On the shorter side and around off. Saud Shakeel punches it to covers this time.
On a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone watchfully.
On a length and around off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it solidly towards the off side.
A fullish delivery and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it back to the bowler.
Serves a beautiful good-length delivery. It is outside off and swings away a bit as Imam-ul-Haq lets it go.
On a good length and angling around off. Imam-ul-Haq is patient enough to let it go again.
On a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone again.
Bowls it fuller and on middle. Saud Shakeel blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed uo nicely on off. Saud Shakeel fends it off the front foot.
Angles it on middle. Saud Shakeel goes back to a delivery, he could have played off the front foot and manages to just about blocks it.
Slower through the air and around off. Saud Shakeel presses forward to defend it.
Touch shorter and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it off the back foot nicely.
Angles a quicker delivery on middle. Saud Shakeel stays back and blocks it again right under his eyes.
On a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone nicely.
Serves it on a length and angles it on off from 'round the wicket. Imam-ul-Haq defends it back to the bowler.
A fullish delivery and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it to the cover fielder.
Angles a length delivery on middle. Imam-ul-Haq fends it towards the mid on fielder.
On a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone carefully.
Short and wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Tossed up and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq shimmies down the track and works it wide of mid on for a single.

Dropped! Touch shorter and outside off. Saud Shakeel goes deep in his crease and tries to punch it towards the off side. However, he gets an outside edge but Blundell behind the stumps fails to catch it.
Bowls it quicker and fuller on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it out.
On off and turning away. Saud Shakeel plays it late and behind square on the off side.
Angles a quicker delivery on middle. Saud Shakeel fends it off the front foot.
Lovely delivery! This one is tossed up, outside off. It turns away and Saud Shakeel resists the temptation to play this one.
Short and around off. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a good length and outside off. Saud Shakeel lets it go.
Serves a fullish delivery and outside off. Southee is getting a bit of reverse as he is taking the ball away from the left-hander but Saud Shakeel is happy to let it go.
Angles a full delivery on middle. Saud Shakeel clips it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length and around off. Saud Shakeel dabs it towards the off side.
A good-length delivery and outside off. Saud Shakeel makes an easy leave.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Short and wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes deep in his crease and cuts it in front of square for a boundary.
FOUR! Another wonderful shot! Touch shorter and around off. Imam-ul-Haq uses the depth of the crease and punches it through wide of mid on for a boundary.

An appeal for a caught behind but the umpire is not interested. However, Southee decides to take the DRS here. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat here. So the original decision stays and Imam-ul-Haq will continue. Coming to the ball - It is pitched outside off and turns away. Imam-ul-Haq presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A slider on middle and leg. Imam-ul-Haq tries to defend it but gets an inside edge onto his pads. There is an apppeal for an LBW though and the umpire makes a right decision of not out.
Very full and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq digs it out.
On off and quicker and Imam-ul-Haq defends it towards the off side.
NO BALL! On a good length and outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves it but it is a NO BALL as Henry oversteps.
Serves it on a length again and bowls it outside off. Saud Shakeel lets it go.
On a good length and outside off. Saud Shakeel with an easy leave.
Bowls it again, outside off and on a length and Saud Shakeel is happy to let it go.
Lands it on a length and around off. Saud Shakeel fends it towards the backward point fielder.
Henry is palying with the patience of Saud Shakeel! Henry bowls it on a good length and around off. Saud Shakeel resists the temptation to leave it. 32 balls now and he is yet to get off the mark!
Same line and length, outside off. Saud Shakeel is patient enough to let it go.
SIX! Imam-ul-Haq gets to his fifty in style! Good clean hit this. Tossed up on middle. Imam-ul-Haq reaches the pitch of the ball and tonks it down the ground for a biggie.
Touch shorter and quicker on off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it from his crease.
Slower through the air, on off. Imam-ul-Haq fends it off the front foot.
On off and turning away from the left-hander. Imam-ul-Haq lets it go.
Bowls it quicker and fuller on off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it out.
Loopy delivery and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq fends it towards the leg side.
On a good length and around off. Saud Shakeel fends it calmly towards the off side.
On a length, on off and Saud Shakeel gets right behind it to block it.
Oh, this one comes back in sharply! Serves it on a good length and outside off. The ball comes into Saud Shakeel as he leaves it. The ball goes just over the off pole.
Back of a length and around off. Sarfaraz Ahmed fends it with soft hands towards the off side.
Serves a fullish delivery, outside off as he hopes that Saud will chase it. However, Saud Shakeel lets it go again.
Goes fuller and on off. Saud Shakeel pushes it to the mid off fielder.
Shortish and around off. Imam-ul-Haq goes deep in his crease and punches it to sweeper cover for a single.
Bowls it touch shorter and on middle and leg. Saud Shakeel clips it to backward square leg.
Tosses it up and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it back to the bowler. 41 balls now for Saud and he is yet to get off the mark.
Now, he gets off the mark! Touch shorter and around off. Saud Shakeel goes deep in his crease and punches it through covers for a couple.
Nice loopy delivery on middle. Saud Shakeel fends it towards the leg side.
Bowls a flighted delivery again, on middle and Saud Shakeel defends it watchfully.
Bangs it short, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and pulls it to square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
A length ball, in the channel. Saud Shakeel eases it to the man at gully off the outer half.
Full length, outside off. Saud Shakeel shuffles and blocks it into covers.
Matt Henry sees the batter come out of the crease and hence bangs it in short. It flies over the batters head.
Full-length ball, tailing back in. Saud Shakeel blocks it out. Just a single off it.
Darted on the pads, Imam-ul-Haq nudges it to mid-wicket.
Loops it up, full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq uses his feet and knocks it down to long on. They take a single.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Saud Shakeel defends it back to the bowler.
Short again, on off. Saud Shakeel goes back and defends solidly.
It is short, turning in from outside off. Saud Shakeel cuts it to cover-point.
Length ball, wide of off. Saud Shakeel chops it to point. The umpire signals a no ball for overstepping.
Floats it up, around off. Saud Shakeel eases it to mid off.
This is outside off, on a length. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone.
On a good length, this one spits off the deck. Imam-ul-Haq leaves it alone for the keeper once agian.
Good length, wide of off. This one holds its line. Imam-ul-Haq has no shot to offer.
It is full, angled in on off. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A single now as Saud Shakeel clips it to mid-wicket.
A short ball, tailing into the batter, on leg stump. Imam-ul-Haq swivels and pulls it to square leg. The batters have enough time to take two runs.
Short ball, outside off. Saud Shakeel punches it to cover.
Short and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel cuts it to right of sweeper cover for a single.
Tosses it up and on off. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to covers this time.
FOUR! Lovely shot! On the shorter side, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq goes deep in his crease and wrists it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Short and punished again! On middle and shorter in length. Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
A fullish delivery, around off. Saud Shakeel pushes it to cover-point.
Tossed up and on middle. Saud Shakeel plays it back to the bowler.
On middle and fuller. Saud Shakeel works it to square leg for a single.
Bowls it flatter and quicker on middle. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it off the front foot.
Touch shorter and around leg. Imam-ul-Haq clips it to backward square leg.
Tosses it up and on middle. Imam-ul-Haq works it through square leg for a single.
Tossed up, wide of off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it towards point.
Around off, Imam-ul-Haq knocks it to backward point.
Loops it up, full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq defends it on his front foot.
Imam-ul-Haq gets on his front foot once again and blocks it out to covers from outside off.
Loops it up, on off, Imam-ul-Haq remains solid in his defense.
A maiden over for Michael Bracewell as Imam-ul-Haq blocks it away.
Full and on off. Saud Shakeel knocks it to mid on.
Floated and on off. Saud Shakeel pushes it to mid off.
Tosses it up, outside off. It grips and turns in. Saud Shakeel flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq tucks it through mid-wicket for a single.
Saud Shakeel uses his feet this time and clips it towards short mid on.

A dot to end the over! This is pushed through quicker, on off. Saud Shakeel presses forward and blocks it into the deck. Now, hardly 3 overs are left before Stumps. WIll the Kiwis be able to break this stand?
On off, defended to silly point.
This is full and driven to short extra cover.
Loops it up, full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq pushes it to point. Imam-ul-Haq ventures out looking for a single but is sent back.
Imam-ul-Haq shuffles and clips it to the leg side from outside off. They take one.
It is full and on off. Saud Shakeel gets it to the left of the man at first slip.
On off, blocked out. Just a single off the over.
Back of a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq pulls it to square leg for one.
A length ball, this pitches outside leg. Saud Shakeel blocks it with full face.
Back of a length, sliding down leg. Saud Shakeel drags his pull down fine leg for one run.
Back of the length, going down leg. Imam-ul-Haq ducks under it.
FOUR! Perfect shot. Back of a length, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes on his back foot and cuts it through covers for a boundary.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Imam-ul-Haq ducks and leaves it alone. Just one over left then. Can the batters remain solid defensively?
Southee serves it on a hard length from around the wicket. This one does carry through to the keeper. Nonetheless, Saud Shakeel makes a good leave by ducking under it.
This length ball is punched off the back foot through covers for two runs. The stand moves to 51.
Back of a length, outside off. This one takes off the deck. Saud Shakeel lets it be.
FOUR! Good shot. It is a short ball, on off. Saud Shakeel swivels and pulls it along the ground. It goes through the gap at square leg for four runs.
Fuller, on off, defended to silly point.
A sharp bouncer, in the channel. Saud Shakeel sways away from the line. So, that will be STUMPS on Day 2.
FOUR! Great start to the morning for Imam-ul-Haq! Matt Henry bowls from 'round the wicket and serves this slightly short and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq cuts this to deep point for four runs.
Goes a touch fuller this time and angled in from outside off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues bowling full and outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq gets a stride forward and strokes this straight to cover.
Bowls this one back of a length once again and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq cuts this to deep point where there is protection now and they take one.
Back to bowling full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel knocks this straight to the cover fielder.
Full once again and attacking the stumps this time. Saud Shakeel blocks this solidly towards mid off.
Michael Bracewell begins with a slightly short ball outside off. Imam-ul-Haq rocks back and cuts this straight to backward point.
Floats this one full and into the batter. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this back towards the bowler.
Flights this full and in line with the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq defends this into the leg side.
Bowls this one quicker in the air, on a shorter length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves this one alone.
Not as short as the previous ball but still outside off. Imam-ul-Haq gets low and guides this to third man for a single.
FOUR! First boundary of the morning for Saud Shakeel! This is slightly short as well and outside off. Saud Shakeel cuts this late with a hint of edge involved and gets it to third man for four runs.

FOUR LEG BYES! This is poor bowling from New Zealand as they are offering easy runs! Matt Henry strays down leg on a good length. Imam-ul-Haq looks to clip this but misses and gets hit on the legs. It is enough to take the ball to fine leg for four extra runs.
Much better line from Matt Henry as he serves this on a good length just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends this towards mid off.
On a good length once again and outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq is happy to leave this one alone.
Goes fuller this time and attacks the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq digs this out towards mid on.
Wild swing from Imam-ul-Haq! Matt Henry bowls this slightly back of a length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq goes hard at the ball but is beaten.
Straighter line bowled on a fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this with a straight bat back towards the bowler.
Michael Bracewell bowls a loopy delivery full and on a leg stump line. Saud Shakeel defends this back towards the bowler.
Continues bowling really full and just outside off. Saud Shakeel knocks this towards cover.
This is slightly short and just outside off. Saud Shakeel rocks back and tucks this towards short leg.
Flights this one full and just outside off, Saud Shakeel taps this towards mid off.
A low full toss bowled in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel punches this straight to the mid off fielder.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off. Saud Shakeel guides this past point for a single and will keep strike.
A sharp bouncer, wide of off. Saud Shakeel lets it be.
Outside off once again, Shakeel makes the leave.
Henry angles it in, wide of off but gets it to shape away off the deck. Saud Shakeel watches it sail past him.
This is full, angled into the batter, on off. Saud Shakeel defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Saud Shakeel makes an easy leave.
It is a good-length delivery, wide of off. Saud Shakeel gets behind the line and defends it with full face. A maiden now for Henry.
Short, outside off. Imam-ul-Haq flicks it to short leg.
Short of a good length, wide of off. Imam-ul-Haq stays back and taps it to point.
Imam-ul-Haq flicks it off his pads towards deep square leg for one.
A single now as this length ball is punched towards point.
Looped up, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Michael Bracewell goes full and on off. Imam-ul-Haq drives it to cover on the up. Just 2 runs come off it.
Matt Henry bowls this on a good length and just outside off, angling into the batter. Saud Shakeel pushes at the ball and gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length and outside off. Imam-ul-Haq dabs this towards the gully fielder.
Continues bowling on a good length and this time attacks the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this towards short mid on.
Angles this into the stumps on a fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq digs this out towards the fielder placed at short mid-wicket.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq defends with a straight bat towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this one outside the off stump on a good length. Imam-ul-Haq is solid in defense as he knocks this towards cover.
Michael Bracewell bowls this slightly short and outside off. Saud Shakeel cuts this towards point but the fielder at backward point dives to his left and makes a good stop.
Flights this one full and just outside off. Saud Shakeel defends this towards cover.
Floated full once again and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel continues to block this into the off side.
Goes full once again and on an off stump line. Saud Shakeel defends this to right of the bowler.
This is full as well and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel is happy to play this back down the pitch on a his front foot.
FOUR! That is beautifully played! Michael Bracewell goes full this time and continues to attack the stumps. Saud Shakeel paddles this towards fine leg and collects for runs.
Matt Henry bowls this one a good length and offers width outside off. Imam-ul-Haq is not tempted and lets this one through to the keeper.
This is angled into the batter on a good length. Imam-ul-Haq tries to clip this leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Continues bowling on a good length but this time outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends this one solidly into the off side.
Goes slightly fuller this time and angles this into the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this towards mid on.
Persists with the outside off stump line. Imam-ul-Haq knocks this back towards the bowler.
Fires a yorker this time on an off stump line. Imam-ul-Haq gets his bat down in time and digs this out back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Ish Sodhi starts from around the wicket to attack the footmarks. He serves this full and outside off. Saud Shakeel goes deep in the crease and blocks this out.
Goes full and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel clips this to the short-leg fielder.
Bowls this quicker in the air and on a fuller length, turning into the batter. Saud Shakeel flicks this towards mid-wicket.
This is slightly short and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel rocks back onto the back foot and punches this towards cover.
Goes really full this time and attacks the stumps. Saud Shakeel digs this out towards mid on.
This is full as well and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel goes deep in the crease and blocks this into the off side.
Tim Southee starts off with a fullish delivery served outside off. Imam-ul-Haq taps this towards cover-point and looks for a single. Saud Shakeel is not interested.
Goes really full once again and offers width outside off. Imam-ul-Haq miscues his shot straight to the cover fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and still wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq gets low and cuts this to deep point for a single.
Goes over the wicket to Saud Shakeel and delivers this on a good length, angling away from outside off. Saud Shakeel is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
This is fuller in length and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel looks to drive but finds the cover fielder.
Full once again and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel knocks this firmly straight to cover. Just a run from Tim Southee's first over.
Ish Sodhi flights this one full and in line with the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq eases this down to long on for a single.
Floats this one full and straight. Saud Shakeel clips this to mid-wicket.

FOUR! That is a wonderfully executed shot! Ish Sodhi continues to bowl full and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel gets into position in a flash and sweeps this towards deep square leg for four runs.
Goes really full on a leg stump line. Saud Shakeel makes room and knocks this towards mid off.
Bowls this on a fuller length and gets the ball to turn back into the stumps. Saud Shakeel goes deep in the crease and just about manages to flick it off his pads towards mid-wicket.
Persists with bowling full and outside off. Saud Shakeel taps this into the offside on the back foot.
Tim Southee bowls this on a good length and angles this in from outside off. Imam-ul-Haq defends this back down the pitch.
Goes really full this time and on an off stump line. Imam-ul-Haq knocks this to the right of the bowler and he gets down to stop the ball.
Continues bowling on a fuller length and just outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq taps this into the offside.
This is on a good length and wide outside the off-pole. Imam-ul-Haq is watchful as he leaves this one alone.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! New Zealand have the breakthrough and it is the big wicket of Imam-ul-Haq as he walks back 17 runs short of what would have been a wonderful century! This is bowled on a good length but wide outside off. Imam-ul-Haq who has been really disciplined so far goes for a wild swing at the ball but does not connect cleanly. Tom Blundell collects the ball behind the wicket and all the players go up in appeal straight away. They are convinced that there is an edge but the umpire thinks otherwise. Tim Southee opts for the review and Imam-ul-Haq looks slightly worried. UltraEdge shows that there is a tiny spike when the ball passes the toe end of the bat and the onfield decision has to be reversed. Pakistan are four wickets down now and with this partnership broken, New Zealand have an opportunity to get some quick wickets.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Tim Southee

Commentary: Tim Southee welcomes Sarfaraz Ahmed with a full delivery attacking the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks this back towards the bowler. A maiden wicket for Tim Southee.
Tossed up, full and on off. Saud Shakeel clips it to square leg and crosses.
Floats it up, on off pole. It grips and turns away sharply. Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to block it out but gets beaten. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and outside off. Ahmed leans in and drives it into covers.
Sarfaraz Ahmed paddles it to deep square leg and crosses.
Quite short, outside off. Saud Shakeel punches it to point for a single now. He moves to 30 now.
A dot to end the over! It is fuller, turning away. Sarfaraz Ahmed presses forward and blocks it into covers.
This is full, shaping across the left-hander. Saud Shakeel leans in and drives it into the gap at covers. The batters take a single.
Length, wide of off. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it to the off side.
Tim Southee fires it full, wide of off, shaping away a touch. Sarfaraz Ahmed strokes it to covers for a single.
Full, wide of off. Saud Shakeel shuffles and dabs it out.
Touch fuller, leaving the left-hander with the angle. Saud Shakeel has no shot to offer.

BEATEN! Tim Southee almost finds the edge once again. It is a length ball, that is angled across the left-hander. Saud Shakeel tries to defend it out by hanging the blade away from his body with any foot movement. He misses and gets beaten on the outside edge. A probing over from Southee comes to an end.
Touch shorter, wide of off. Sarfaraz Ahmed stays back and punches it through the line towards point.

This is full, sliding down leg. Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to block it on his front foot but gets rapped on his pads. Ish Sodhi puts in a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They do not take the review here.
This is driven through covers for a single.
Another single now as this full delivery is clipped to square leg.
On middle and leg. Ahmed goes back and knocks it to mid on.
Loops it up, around off. Ahmed gets forward to dab it down.
Tim Southee serves it on a length, around off. Saud Shakeel blocks it firmly.
Good length, shaping away from outside off. Saud Shakeel watches the ball sail past him.
Touch fuller, on off. Saud Shakeel gets across and clips it to the left of mid on.
Another dot now! It is full, angling across the left-hander. Shakeel leans in and drives it into covers.
Outside off, left alone.
Tim Southee records his fifth maiden of the innings! Once again the seamer serves it wide of off, on a length and Saud Shakeel lets it be.
It is full and on middle. Ahmed sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
On off, clipped to mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played! A much-needed boundary. It is tossed up, outside off, turning into the left-hander. Saud Shakeel gets down on one knee and slogs it over mid-wicket for a cracking boundary.
Tossed up, full and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it on his front foot.
It is tossed up, full and outside off. Saud Shakeel gets low and sweeps it towards deep square leg. One taken.
This is pushed through quicker, attacking the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks it away in time.
Southee starts with a full one, shaping across the left-hander. Left alone.
Fuller once again, wide of off. Saud Shakeel gets across and knocks it to covers.
A little bit of reverse now on offer. This is full, comes in a bit into the left-hander. Saud Shakeel blocks it to mid on.
On a good length, outside off. Shakeel shoulders his arms at it.
Five dots on the trot! Goes full, around off, shaping away. Shakeel opens the face and works it into cover.
Sixth maiden for Tim Southee now, as Saud Shakeel drives this full delivery straight to the man at mid off.
Tossed up, outside off. Ahmed uses his feet and pads it out.
BEAUTY! It is looped up, around off. It grips and turns away a long way. Sarfaraz Ahmed is drawn into it and tries to have a poke at it. He gets lucky here to not get the edge.
Short, wide of off. Sarfaraz Ahmed cuts it to backward point.
This is flicked off his pads towards square leg. They take one.
Tossed up, on off. Saud Shakeel presses forward and blocks it into the deck.
Flatter and outside off. Saud Shakeel defends it out.
Tim Southee bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes at this an gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
This is bowled slightly fuller and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel shuffles away and slaps this to deep cover for a single.

FOUR! Lovely timing from Sarfaraz Ahmed as he hits this with great control! Tim Southee bowls this full and offers width outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed strokes this towards deep cover and the ball keeps running towards the boundary for four runs.
Goes really full this time and angles the ball into the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks this out towards mid-wicket.

Another full delivery served just outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed knocks this back towards the bowler and Tim Southee shows some aggression as he picks up the ball before taking aim at the stumps. Misses the batter and the stumps as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Bowls this one on a good length and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed is watchful this time as he leaves this one alone.
Ish Sodhi bowls a loopy delivery full and outside off. Saud Shakeel dabs the ball towards point and takes a single.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed rocks back and punches this straight to cover.

FOUR! Sarfaraz Ahmed looking to be aggressive here and Ish Sodhi bowls a really poor delivery! A low full toss served outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed is down the wicket and has to adjust his shot but manages to fine the gap and gets the ball to deep mid-wicket for four runs.
Bowls a googly full and just outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed charges down the wicket and misses the ball. Gets hit on the pads and rushes back into the crease.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards fine leg for a single.
This is slightly short and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel plays this towards point and takes a single to keep strike.
Matt Henry begins this spell with a good length delivery served outside off and angling further away. Saud Shakeel steps across to the off side and shoulders arms to the ball.
This is on a good length as well and just outside off. Saud Shakeel taps this towards cover-point with soft hands and takes a single.
Matt Henry continues to bowl on a good length but offers width outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed strokes this with pure timing and very little power towards deep cover-point and they take three runs.
Bowls this way outside the off stump on a good length. Saud Shakeel is content with leaving this one alone.

Goes slightly fuller and gets this closer to the off pole. The angle takes the ball away from the batter but Saud Shakeel is drawn into playing the shot. He gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Angles this away from the left-hander once again but this is wide outside off on a good length. Saud Shakeel raises his arms and leaves the ball alone.
Ish Sodhi bowls a googly slightly short and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed mistimes his shot on the back foot towards mid one.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed goes for the sweep shot this time and gets the ball to deep square leg for a run.
Floats this one full and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel takes a good stride forward and clips the ball towards mid-wicket.
A loopy delivery this time bowled well outside off. Saud Shakeel rocks back in his crease and blocks this with a straight bat back down the pitch.
Goes full this time and strays onto the pads. Saud Shakeel clips this towards deep backward square leg and collects a single.
Another flighted delivery bowled outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed gets his front foot to the pitch of the ball and defends it towards cover.
Matt Henry starts with a good-length delivery angling away from outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves this one alone.
Continues bowling outside the off stump on a good length. Saud Shakeel is happy to shoulder arms to these balls.
This is even wider outside the off pole and on a fuller length. Saud Shakeel does not even bother raising his bat to this one as it goes through to the keeper.
Much better from Matt Henry as he bowls this closer to the stumps on a good length. Saud Shakeel has to play at this and blocks the ball towards cover.
This is going away from the off stump on a good length. Saud Shakeel feels for the ball this time and gets beaten all ends up.
Delivers this in line with the stumps on a good length. Saud Shakeel defends this solidly to the left of the bowler.
Ish Sodhi floats a googly full and just outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed taps this towards cover.

FOUR! A lucky boundary but Sarfaraz Ahmed does really well here! Ish Sodhi sees the batter ready to charge down the wicket and fires this one full and wide. Sarfaraz Ahmed is down the pitch and has to reach for the ball but manages to edge this towards deep backward point for four runs.
Bowls this one quickly as well and in line with the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed shimmies down once again but misses the ball. It goes off his pads into the leg side.

FOUR! Sarfaraz Ahmed is playing spine really well here! Ish Sodhi drags this one short and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed this time waits back in the crease and punches this towards deep cover for four more runs.
A low full toss this time outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed misses out as he knocks this straight to mid off.

A lovely delivery to end the over! This is on a fuller length and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed is stuck in the crease and pushes at the ball but gets beaten on the outside edge by some sharp turn.
Matt Henry bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Saud Shakeel blocks this towards cover.
Goes slightly fuller this time and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel gets his front foot slightly out of the way and defends this towards the cover fielder.

A massive appeal from Matt Henry and the umpire remains still. Tim Southee has been convinced to go up for the review. This is bowled on a good length and aimed for the stumps. Saud Shakeel misses his defensive shot and gets hit on the pads. They check UltraEdge and there is no bat involved but Ball Tracking shows that it is pitching outside leg and also missing the stumps. Poor review taken and New Zealand have just one remaining now.
Bowls this one full and just outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel strokes this to the right of mid off and takes a quick single.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed knocks this on the up towards cover.
Goes fuller this time and outside the off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed digs this out back to the bowler's left.
Ish Sodhi starts off with a loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Saud Shakeel rocks back in the crease and blocks this into the off side.
Gets the ball to turn into the batter from a shorter length, outside off. Saud Shakeel tucks this towards deep backward square leg and takes a single.
Bowls this quick and short into the batter. Sarfaraz Ahmed transfers his weight onto the back foot and knocks this to the right of mid on for a run.
Floats this one full and into the pads. Saud Shakeel clips this towards mid on.
A loopy delivery this time full and outside off. Saud Shakeel mistimes his shot straight to short cover.
Goes full once again and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel strokes this to the right of the cover fielder and takes a single to retain strike.
Ajaz Patel starts off with a full delivery outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel defends this back towards the bowler.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps, Saud Shakeel knocks this to the left of the bowler.
Bowls this one full as well and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel taps this down into the pitch on the back foot.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. This is dabbed into the off side.
Goes straighter this time and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel defends this on the front foot back to the bowler.
Goes really full this time and on the pads. Saud Shakeel clips this towards mid-wicket.
Ish Sodhi flights this one full and just outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed plays this to the right of the bowler and takes a single.
Bowls this full and gets it to spin into the pads. Saud Shakeel tucks this towards backward square leg.
This is slightly short and outside off, turning into the batter. Saud Shakeel dabs this towards short leg.
FOUR! That has been swept away in style! Ish Sodhi loops this one full and outside off. Saud Shakeel is down on one knee and he hits it towards deep backward square leg for four runs.
Another loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Saud Shakeel strokes this through covers for a couple of runs.
Short once again and outside off, Saud Shakeel gets across the stumps and blocks it back down the pitch.
Angles this one full and down leg side. Sarfaraz Ahmed chooses to leave this one alone as it is collected by the keeper.
Goes full and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed paddles this towards fine leg and takes a single.
Floats this one full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel gets forward and clips this to the left of mid on for a run.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed goes on the front foot and defends this back towards the bowler.

FOUR! Pakistan looking to be much more positive in this session! Ajaz Patel bowls this well outside the off stump on a fuller length. Sarfaraz Ahmed reaches for it and sweeps it towards deep square leg for four runs.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! This one is a bit lucky but Pakistan will take it. Ajaz Patel flights this one full and wide outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed attempts the sweep shot once again but this time gets a top edge that flies over the keeper to his right for four more runs.
Ish Sodhi goes over the wicket to the left-hander now and bowls this short, in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel tucks this towards square leg.
This is short as well and on a leg stump line. Saud Shakeel rocks back in the crease and plays this behind square on the leg side for a single.
This is really short and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed misses out as he pulls this wide of mid on but Kane Williamson dives to his right and stops a boundary. They take a single.
Continues bowling short and on a leg stump line. Saud Shakeel clips this towards mid-wicket.
A googly this time bowled short and spinning away from the left-hander, outside off. Saud Shakeel dabs this towards point and takes a quick run.

FOUR! This has been punched with great timing! Ish Sodhi continues bowling short and just outside the off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed moves across the stumps and thumps this down towards long on for four runs. Kane Williamson at mid on makes a valiant attempt to dive and stop the ball but does not get to it.
Ajaz Patel bowls this full and outside off. Saud Shakeel clips this to the left of the bowler.
Slightly short this time and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel tucks this into the leg side.
FOUR! Great uses of the feel from Saud Shakeel! Ajaz Patel flights this one full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel charges down the wicket and lofts this towards long on for four runs.
Pulls his length back this time and serves this in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel goes back in the crease and works this to deep square leg or a single.
Full this time and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed sweeps this weel but finds the deep square leg fielder. Has to settle for a run.
This is in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Saud Shakeel gets his front foot forward and defends this back towards the bowler.
Tim Southee starts off with a back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed pulls this straight to mid-wicket.
Bowls this on a good length and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed shuffles forward and taps this towards short cover who misfields allowing them to take a quick single.
This is on a fuller length and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel clips this towards square leg.
Goes full once again and just outside off. Saud Shakeel covers the line of the ball and defends this solidly towards cover.
Really full this time and attacking the stumps. Saud Shakeel flicks this towards mid on.
Bowls this one on a good length and wide outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel moves his bat inside the line of the ball and leaves it alone.
Matt Henry begins the over with a full delivery just outside the off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed punches this down the ground and they take three runs as the mid on fielder gives chase and stops the ball.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel blocks this solidly towards short cover fielder.
Bangs this in short and outside off. Saud Shakeel gets well on top of the bounce and pulls this towards deep mid-wicket. There is a fielder placed there and they get just a single.
Goes full this time and serves this outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends this to the left of the bowler.
Full once again and closer to the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed is solid in defense as he blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
On a good length this time and outside the off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed uses his wrists and clips this wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Tim Southee bowls this full and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed gets across and flicks this towards mid on. He looks for a single but this is hit straight to the fielder. A loud shout of no.
This is full as well and wide outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed is moving his feet as well as he gets forward to tap this towards cover.
This is angled down leg on a fuller length. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to glance this but misses as the ball goes through to the keeper.

Straying down leg once again on a fuller length. Sarfaraz Ahmed looks to flick this fine but misses and the ball seems to clip his pad before going to the keeper. A huge appeal from Tim Southee but does not opt for a review.
Full once again and angled into the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends this towards mid-wicket.
That is FIFTY for Sarfaraz Ahmed! He gets there in just 61 deliveries. On a good length this time and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed works this through point and rushes across for a single.
Matt Henry bowls this back of a length and bowls this into the batter. Sarfaraz Ahmed does well to fend this back into the pitch on the leg side.
Bangs this in short and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed gets on his toes and pulls this towards deep square leg for a single.

On a good length this time and just outside off. Saud Shakeel transfers his weight on the back foot and strokes this to the right of point. Ajaz Patel makes a good stop diving to his right and restricts the batters to a  single.
Continues bowling on a good length and in line with the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes a tad bit fuller and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed miscues his shot straight to the mid off fielder.
Back to bowling on a good length and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks this firmly towards cover.
Michael Bracewell begins this spell with a shortish delivery outside off. Saud Shakeel improvises and gets across the stumps to paddle this towards fine leg for a couple of runs.
Goes fuller this time and serves this outside off. Saud Shakeel defends this towards point.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel strokes this towards deep point and takes a run.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed shimmies down the wicket and knocks this down to long on for a single.
Bowls this short and angled into the stumps. Saud Shakeel goes deep in the crease and blocks this towards the off side.
Gives the ball more air, and tosses it outside off on a fuller length. Saud Shakeel gets his front foot forward and leaves the ball alone.
Henry serves it on a length ball, attacking the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed stays back, closes the face and blocks it out.
Ahmed presses forward to this full delivery and blocks it into covers.
Fuller, on fourth stump. Ahmed defends it out under his eyes.
Touch fuller, angling away from off. Sarfaraz Ahmed comes forward and digs it back to the bowler.
Full length, on fifth stump. Ahmed comes forward and defends it into the deck.
Fraction short, in the channel. Ahmed goes on his toes and punches it through point for a single. He retains the strike here.
Sarfaraz Ahmed rotates the strike instantly as he flicks this full delivery through the gap at mid-wicket.
Michael Bracewell floats it up, full and on middle, coming in with the arm. Saud Shakeel defends by getting forward.
Saud Shakeel makes room for this full delivery, on off and drives it to point, not in the gap though.
Michael Bracewell drags his length ball, outside off. Saud Shakeel taps it towards cover-point.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! Michael Bracewell overpitches it wide outside off. Saud Shakeel frees his arms and carves it through the gap at the cover region. Boundary.
On middle, defended to the left of the bowler off the outer half.
Fuller in length, on off. Ahmed taps it to point.
Goes full again, around off. Ahmed drives it away from mid off which allows them to take a quick single.
Back of a length, on the body. Saud Shakeel pulls it along the ground to deep square leg for a single.
An inswinger, full and on off. Ahmed defends it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on top of off. Ahmed blocks it out watchfully.
A full toss now, on middle and leg. Sarfaraz Ahmed whips it to the leg side but straight to the fielder.
Michael Bracewell starts with a floater, around off. Saud Shakeel taps it away.
This is darted on the pads. Saud Shakeel goes back and clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
It is tossed up, wide of off. Sarfaraz Ahmed gets across and blocks.
It is fuller, outside off, turning in. Sarfaraz Ahmed prods and defends.
Sarfaraz Ahmed now uses his feet and whips this full ball to the man at mid on.
It is short, turning in from outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed uses the depth of his crease to play it back to the bowler. New Zealand have managed to put a lid over the scoring rate here.
Southee serves a length ball, wide of off. Saud Shakeel shuffles and steers it to the left of gully. The fielder there is quick to move to hie left and gather the ball with two hands.
This is punched to deep point off the back foot by Saud Shakeel. One taken.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Good length, wide of off. Sarfaraz Ahmed taps it out and looks for a single but his partner denies.
Third dot in a row! It is a length ball, moving away a bit, in the channel. Sarfaraz Ahmed works it to cover.
Another dot now to end the over. It is touch fuller, on off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed eases it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off, blocked out on the front foot.
Full, in-line with the stumps. Defended back to the bowler.
On off, blocked out.
Short, around off, punched to mid off.
Tosses it up, on off. Saud Shakeel defends it on his front foot.

FOUR! And with this boundary the stand for the fifth wicket moves to 102 runs. This partnership has started to hurt the Kiwis here. It is pushed through quicker and on middle. Saud Shakeel looks to go for the sweep but gets a top edge on it. The ball flies over the slip fielder and races away to the fence.
A single now as this length ball is punched through point.
On a length, around off. Saud Shakeel gets an inside edge to mid-wicket. The batters cross for a single.
This is full, outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends it to cover and takes a single.

FOUR! EDGY! Tim Southee comes 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, angling in from outside off. Saud Shakeel tries to defend but gets a thick outside edge. Although as he defends it with soft hands, it dies as he time it reaches the slip fielder, who has to make a full-stretched dive to his left but is uable to get to the ball. The ball races away to the third man fence.
Good-length ball, outside off. Saud Shakeel defends it out.
It is a length ball, wide of off. Saud Shakeel has no shot to offer.
This is worked to long on for a single.
Fuller, on middle. Saud Shakeel tucks it to the leg side.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel defends this back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery served full and outside off. Saud Shakeel strokes this into the gap towards deep cover for a couple of runs.
Tossed up, full and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it into the deck.
Saud Shakeel gets on his front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Full, going down leg. Ahmed sweeps it behind square on the leg side for an easy single.
A bit short, around off. Saud Shakeel shuffles and tucks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Exceptional shot! It is fuller and quicker, outside off. Saud Shakeel prods and sweeps it along the ground through square leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Saud Shakeel finds the boundary once again. This time he takes the aerial route. It is full and on off. Saud Shakeel dances down the track and wrists it over mid on for four more. He moves to 90.
On off, defended out watchfully.
This is spilled way outside off, Saud Shakeel shuffles across and almost reaches the tramline as he makes the leave.
Sarfaraz Ahmed uses his feet and defends it back to the bowler.
It is short, outside off. Ahmed taps it to point and crosses.
Loops it up, around off, blocked out.
Full, attacking the stumps. Saud Shakeel presses forward and fends it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Shakeel punches it to point off the back foot.
Pushed through full and on off. Saud Shakeel defends it back to Michael Bracewell.
Full, outside off. Ahmed blocks it into covers.
FOUR! Nicely played. Slower through the air, full and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed rocks back and cuts it wide of point for four runs.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Ajaz Patel goes full and outside the off pole, Sarfaraz Ahmed gets well forward and sweeps this towards deep backward square leg for four runs.
Floated full and outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed shimmies down the wicket and clips the ball towards long on for a single.
Looped up full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel gets this off his inside edge towards short fine leg.

FOUR! Slashed hard and gets a boundary! Ajaz Patel bowls this short and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel cuts it uppishly and gets a thick outside edge over the slip fielder for the third boundary of the over.
Michael Bracewell flights this one full and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed flicks this to the right of mid on and takes a quick single.
Good turn on offer here all of a sudden! This is floated full and outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves this one alone.
Gets this closer to the stumps on a fullish length. Saud Shakeel goes back in the crease and just about manages to keep it out.
This is slightly short and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel rocks back and punches this towards cover-point.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel defends this towards point.
Tosses this one full and in line with the stumps. Takes a thickish edge and goes just past the silly point fielder.
Ajaz Patel floats this full and in line with the stumps. Sarfaraz Ahmed blocks this back down the pitch.
Another loopy delivery served full and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed defends this into the off side.
This is slightly short and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed waits on it and punches this to deep cover-point for a single.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps on a shorter length. Saud Shakeel clips this towards square leg and takes a quick run.
Flights this one full and just outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed pushes forward and gets an inside edge to square leg.
Tosses this one full outside off, Sarfaraz Ahmed sweeps to behind square on the leg side and takes a single to keep strike.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Sarfaraz Ahmed gets across and flicks this to backward square leg for a run.

FOUR! That is an excellent shot and gets Saud Shakeel to 99! Michael Bracewell flights this one full and outside off. Saud Shakeel gets forward and sweeps this towards deep square leg for a cracking boundary.

That is HUNDRED for Saud Shakeel! What an outstanding knock from the Pakistan batter and he has paced this inning perfectly! Michael Bracewell tosses this full and outside off. Saud Shakeel taps this towards cover and takes a quick single. He punches the air in celebration.
FOUR! Sarfaraz Ahmed joins the party! Michael Bracewell bowls this full and outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed is down the wicket in a flash and lofts this back over the bowler's head for four runs.
Angles this one into the stumps on a fuller length. Sarfaraz Ahmed clips this towards square leg and gets across for a single.
This is short and outside off. Saud Shakeel rocks back and cuts this towards backward point.

A loud appeal for lbw and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Daryl Mitchell is pumped up and rightly so! Sarfaraz Ahmed is quick to take the review. Coming to the delivery, it is a length ball that nips in from outside off. Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to block it out but gets pinged on his pads. Daryl Mitchell pleads and the umpire agrees. Although, the celebration is cut short as the UltraEdge confirms that the bat is involved and the decision has to be overturned.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Ahmed clips it to the leg side.

OUT! STUMPED! Some exceptional glovework from Tom Blundell has provided his side with a much-needed breakthrough. Fuller, sliding down leg. Ahmed misses his flick. The keeper gathers it cleanly and whips the bails off. The square leg umpire takes it upstais to confirm. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The side-on angle suggests that Sarfaraz Ahmed gets his back foot inside the crease, but it looks like Ahmed lifts his leg a touch once the keeper takes the bails off. This is going to be close. New Zealand players are already celebrating here as there seems to be some gap between the foot and the floor. The third umpire though is still having a closer look at it. The big screen shows OUT! WOW! Just incredible. Daryl Mitchell strikes on his third delivery and Sarfaraz Ahmed has to walk back on 78 runs. He will be surely gutted. New Zealand have a sniff here.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Daryl Mitchell

Commentary: Full length, on off. Defended out solidly.
Fuller, on off, blocked out.
This is full, attacking the stumps. Agha Salman squares up a touch as he defends it out.
On off, pushed to covers for one.
Floats it up, wide of off. Salman drives it into covers.
Looped up, full and on off. Salman blocks it on his front foot.
This is tossed up, wide of off. Salman prods and gets it to the right of slip fielder off the outside edge. It does not carry though.
On off, blocked out on the front foot.
FOUR! Beautiful shot. Agha Salman opens his account with a boundary. It is full and outside off. Agha Salman carves it through covers for four runs. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3.
Matt Henry starts off after the break with a delivery bowled back of a length and just outside off. Saud Shakeel fends this into the off side.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel dabs this towards the gully fielder.
Pulls his length back slightly once again and bowls this outside off. Saud Shakeel blocks this towards point.
Slightly short and on an off stump line. Saud Shakeel judges the length well and raises his arms to leave the ball alone.
This is in a good length and angling away from outside off. Saud Shakeel is happy to shoulder his arms to this one as well.
Goes really full this time and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel punches this towards mid on. A maiden to start proceedings in the final session of the day.
Daryl Mitchell begins with a good-length delivery drifting into the stumps. Agha Salman blocks this towards mid on.
Goes fuller and into the pads. Agha Salman manages to keep this out back down the pitch.
Bowls this full as well and angling down leg. Agha Salman dabs this towards short mid-wicket.
On a good length this time and just outside the off stump. Agha Salman defends this towards short cover.
Decides to bowl full once again and angles this in from outside off. Agha Salman knocks this back towards the bowler.
First runs of the session! Daryl Mitchell strays onto the pads on a fuller length. Agha Salman clips this to the left of mid-wicket and they take a couple of runs.
Matt Henry bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel taps this into the pitch and the ball rolls towards gully.
This one is a touch fuller and outside off. Saud Shakeel looks to drive with very little leg movement and gets beaten.
Bowls this on a good length and on an off stump line. Saud Shakeel looks to block but gets an inside edge onto his pads and the ball rolls towards backward point.
On a good length once again and outside off. Saud Shakeel raises his arms and leaves the ball alone.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel gets across the line of the ball and defends this into the off side.
Goes fuller this time and angles this away from the left-hander from outside off. Saud Shakeel shoulders arms to this one.
Strays down leg side on a fuller length. Agha Salman misses his flick and Tom Blundell does well to get across to stop the ball.

FOUR! This has been beautifully driven! Daryl Mitchell bowls this on a good length and outside off. Agha Salman gets his front foot forward and strokes this on the up towards deep cover-point for four runs.
Goes a touch fuller and still outside the off stump. Agha Salman defends this solidly back towards the bowler.
Really full this time and angled into the stumps. Agha Salman is watchful as he digs this out on his front foot towards cover.
Fires in a yorker this time aimed for the leg stump Agha Salman gets his bat down in time and manages to keep this out.
This one nips back in sharply from a good length and outside off. Agha Salman pushes at it and gets an inside edge towards mid-wicket.
Matt Henry bowls this full and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel lets this go through to the keeper.
Goes full once again and on the pads. Saud Shakeel flicks this wide of mid on and takes a single.
This is on a good length and just outside off. Nips back in after pitching and Agha Salman manages to keep it out towards point.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside off. Agha Salman shoulders his arms and leaves it alone.
Bowls this one full and outside off. Agha Salman looks to drive through the off side but miscues it towards mid-wicket.
Attacks the stumps on a fuller length at 133 clicks. Agha Salman knocks this back towards the bowler.
Daryl Mitchell bowls a loose delivery to the left-hander. This is short and really wide outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves this one alone.
This is full but still way outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel continues to be patient and let it through to the keeper.
This seems like a plan. Daryl Mitchell continues to ball wide outside off on a good length. Saud Shakeel keeps leaving it alone.
On a good length and angling further away after pitching well outside off. Saud Shakeel shows good concentration as this goes through to the keeper as well.
Fuller this time and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel does not move and just raises his bat.
A full over where the ball has been left alone. Daryl Mitchell continues to tempt the batter wide outside off on a fuller length. Saud Shakeel steps across and then leaves this one.
Matt Henry bowls this on a good length and just outside the off pole. Agha Salman shows that he can leave the ball as well.
On a good length once again and outside the off stump. Agha Salman comes forward and blocks this towards cover.
Goes full this time and offers width outside off. Agha Salman goes through with the shot and gets an inside edge towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Back to bowling on a good length and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel keeps this out solidly.
Bangs this one in short but well down leg side. Saud Shakeel initially shapes up to pull but then decides against it.
Gets this one to angle away from the left-hander on a good length and outside off. Saud Shakeel raises his arms and lets the keeper collect the ball.
Daryl Mitchell bowls this full and angled in from outside off. Agha Salman blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues bowling full and on an outside off stump line. Agha Salman showing good defense as this is tapped towards cover.
Gets this straighter and on a good length. Agha Salman defends this with a straight bat back down the pitch.
Goes back to bowling full and outside the off stump. Agha Salman dabs this towards point and takes a single.
Back to the outside off stump strategy to the left-hander, and this is served on a good length. Saud Shakeel knows the plan and leaves this one alone.
This is a touch fuller and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel is behind the line of the ball as he blocks this towards cover.
Tim Southee begins this spell with the keeper up to the stumps. He bowls this full and at the stumps, Agha Salman digs this out back towards the bowler.
Goes full once again angled into the pads. Agha Salman taps this towards short mid-wicket
Gets this to nip back in from a fuller length and just outside off. Agha Salman looks to block but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump. Agha Salman defends this towards point.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside the off stump. Agha Salman looks to punch this away but gets an inside edge back down into the pitch.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump. Agha Salman knocks this towards cover-point. Maiden to start off this spell for Tim Southee.
Ish Sodhi bowls from 'round the wicket to the southpaw. Gets this to spin into the batter from outside off on a shorter length. Saud Shakeel dabs this towards short leg.

Gets this to turn sharply on a fuller length from outside off. Saud Shakeel gets across the stumps and looks to clip the leg side. The ball balloons off the pads into the hands of short leg. There is a huge appeal but the umpire remains unmoved.
This is slightly short and outside off. Saud Shakeel rocks back and punches this towards cover.
Goes full this time and gets it to spin into the stumps. Saud Shakeel goes back in the crease and just about manages to keep it out.
This is floated in full and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel gets a long stride forward and defends this back to the bowler.
Bowls this one slightly short and into the stumps. Saud Shakeel taps this down towards short leg.
Tim Southee bowls this full and wide outside the off stump. Agha Salman reaches for it and taps it towards point.
Goes full once again and outside off. Some shape away from the batter as Agha Salman blocks this towards point.
Continues bowling full and angles this one down leg. Agha Salman looks to clip this towards the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads.
This is on a good length and well outside the off stump. Agha Salman works this into the gap towards deep backward point and adds three runs to his kitty.

DROPPED! A massive chance goes begging! Tom Latham has very good hands but he has dropped a sitter! This is bowled on a good length and outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel pushes at this away from his body and gets a thick outside edge that goes towards the short point fielder who was placed there just before this ball. Tom Latham goes to grab this with a reverse cup but it spills out of his hands.
This is on a good length as well but way outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel does not offer a shot.
Ish Sodhi bowls this full and outside the off pole. Agha Salman drives this towards deep cover for a single.
Bowls this on full and spinning down leg. Saud Shakeel clips this down to fine leg for a run.
A loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Agha Salman knocks this back past the bowler and Kane Williamson does well at mid off to dive and restrict the batters to a single.
This is spinning into the stumps from outside off on a fuller length. Saud Shakeel flicks this towards deep square leg for one.
Bowls this slightly short and outside the off stump. Agha Salman stands tall and blocks this towards cover.
Floats this one full and outside the off pole. Agha Salman gets a good stride forward and defends this into the off side.
Tim Southee bowls this full and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel raises his bat and leaves it alone.
Goes full this time and on the pads. Saud Shakeel flicks this towards deep square leg for a single.
Bowls this one full as well and outside the off stump. Agha Salman defends this solidly back towards the bowler.
