This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Agha Salman taps this towards point.

FOUR! Much-needed runs for Pakistan as they get their first boundary in 10 overs! This is on a good length but wide outside the off pole. Agha Salman strokes this towards deep backward point and collects four runs.
Bowls this one fuller and outside the off stump. Agha Salman defends this solidly to the cover fielder.
This is darted on the pads, Saud Shakeel clips it to mid-wicket.
Loops it up, full and outside off. Saud Shakeel shuffles and flicks it to the leg side once again.
A single now as this is pushed through the off side.
It is tossed up, outside off. It grips and turns away sharply. Agha Salman tries to have a poke at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
FOUR! Floats it up through the air, full and on off. Salman drills it through covers for a fine boundary.
Outside off, defended out watchfully.
Southee goes full and wide outside off. Shakeel reaches out and pushes it into covers. There is a misfield and the batters cross.
This is full, sliding down leg. Salman nudges it to square leg.
An inswinging delivery, full and on off. Salman blocks it back to the bowler.
Full, tailing into the pads, Salman prods and blocks it back to the pacer.
Length, outside off, moving in late. Salman dabs it to point.
On the pads, clipped to the leg side.
Full and outside off, turning in. Saud Shakeel defends it out.
Loops it up, wide of off. Shakeel blocks it on his front foot.
This is dirven past mid off for one.
On off, blocked out.
Floats it up, wide outside off, turning away. Salman lets it be.
This is outside off. Salman prods and defends it towards point.
Good length, around off. Saud Shakeel defends it solidly.
A length ball, angling across the left-hander. Saud Shakeel makes a good leave.
Tim Southee angles it away from the left-hander once again. It is far away from Saud Shakeel to even bother him.
Fuller, on the pads, Saud Shakeel flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
This is full, outside off. Agha Salman gets it to square leg off the inside edge.
An inswinging delivery, full and on middle. Agha Salman blocks it with a straight bat.
This is pushed through quicker, full and on off. Saud Shakeel blocks it with full face.
Sodhi drags his length back, outside off. Saud Shakeel taps it to the off side.

LEG BYE! A stifled appeal for lbw but turned down. This is tossed up, around off, it grips and turns down leg. Saud Shakeel gets pinged on his back thigh pads. as the ball rolls to square leg. The batters collect a leg bye.
Looped up, around off, defended out.
Outside off, left alone.
It is full, wide outside off. Agha Salman reaches out and steers it towards gully.
It is a length ball, moving away from the left-hander. Saud Shakeel has no shot to offer.
Fuller, outside off. Saud Shakeel gets across and blocks.
Goes full again, wide of off. Saud Shakeel comes forward and drives it to mid off.
This one is served, outside off. Saud Shakeel lets it be.
It is a length ball, wide of off. This one stays low off the deck. Saud Shakeel keeps his bat to himself.
On a length, wide of off. Saud Shakeel lets it through to the keeper. A maiden for Daryl Mitchell.

Good running! It is full and outside off. Agha Salman prods and taps it to covers. He takes off to the other end. Henry Nicholls collects and scores a direct hit at the striker's end. The replays confirm that Saud Shakeel had his bat grounded.
A single now as this is pushed into the off side.
Full and on leg. Salman sweeps it to deep square leg and crosses. Three singles on the trot.
Make that four singles as Saud Shakeel comes down the track and taps this full delivery to the right of mid on.
On off, defended out.
Agha Salman flicks this length ball off his pads. It goes through square leg. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
A length ball, angled across the left-hander, outside off. It moves further away which makes it easy for Shakeel to make the leave.
Outside off once again. Saud Shakeel lets it through.
Full length, around off. Much closer to Shakeel. He blocks it on his front foot this time.
On a good length, wide outside off. Saud Shakeel leaves it alone. This is his 305th delivery. It has been a gitty knock by the Pakistani batter.
A length ball, that lands around off and leaves the batter. Saud Shakeel is happy to have a sighter.
On a length, leaving the left-hander once again. Saud Shakeel deals with it with ease and sees off the over with another sighter.
FOUR! A surprise boundary for Pakistan! Ish Sodhi floats this one full and wide outside off. Agha Salman goes for the expansive drive and drills this to deep point for four runs.
A loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Agha Salman blocks this towards cover.
Goes 'round the wicket to the right-hander and serves this full, outside leg. Agha Salman pads this away.
Continues bowling outside leg stump on a fuller length. Agha Salman offers no shot and lets the ball hit his pad.
Bowls a googly in line with the stump. Agha Salman gets forward and blocks this into the off side.
FOUR! Two boundaries in the over! Ish Sodhi floats this full and on a leg stump line. Agha Salman makes room and strokes this towards long on for four runs.
Daryl Mitchell bowls this full and wide outside off. Saud Shakeel continues to leave balls that are along that line.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel continues to be watchful as he lets this through.
Goes really full and just outside the off pole. Saud Shakeel digs this out towards mid off.
Fuller this time and slightly outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel defends this solidly towards short cover.
A tad bit fuller and still well outside the line of the stumps on the off side. Saud Shakeel raises his arms and lets it through.
Continues bowling full and on an off stump line. Saud Shakeel taps this towards short cover.
Patel comes 'round the wicket and serves it full, coming in with the arm on off. Salman defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Top shot! It is tossed up, full and outside off. Salman dances down the track and lofts it over mid off for a boundary. The stand also moves to 50 now.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Ajaz Patel gets his second wicket and has broken the stand which was cutting down the deficit for run. Brilliant catch by Michael Bracewell at first slip, he gathers it on his second attempt. It is looped up, full and outside off. Agha Salman gets down on one knee and goes for the sweep. All he manages to get is a top edge. The ball lobs to the right of Michael Bracewell at first slip. The fielder dives to his right and gets a hand on it but it spills out, although Michael Bracewell keeps his eyes on the ball and makes the most of the second bite.
Howout: c Michael Bracewell b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Full, outside off, defended out.
Around off, Ali blocks it out solidly.
Bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Hasan Ali digs this out back towards the bowler.
Very full, wide of off, left alone.
Length ball, on off. Shakeel defends it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. Shakeel shoulders his arms at it.
It is full, on off stump. Shakeel gets it to the off side off the outer half.
Mitchell goes full again, wide outside off. Shakeel drives it towards point.
FOUR! UP AND OVER! It is overpitced, just outside off. Saud Shakeel gets under it and lofts it over extra cover for a fine boundary.

FOUR! Almost a catch!. It is a short ball, outside off. Ali goes back and smashes it high to the left of the man at mid off. Matt Henry there moves to his left, puts in a full-stretched dive and manages to get two hands on it mid-air, although it is hit powerfully and races away to the boundary.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ajaz Patel gets another wicket here. Hasan Ali holes out this time. It is a short ball, around off. Ali rocks back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket. The ball goes very high in the air, but it is hit straight down the throat of Devon Conway in the deep. He juggles it once before pouching it safely near the ropes. Pakistan are falling apart here.
Howout: c Devon Conway b Ajaz Patel

Commentary: Angled in full, into the pads. Shah blocks it back to the bowler.
Full, and on off. Shah dabs it down.
Pushed through quicker and on off. Shah blocks it to silly point.

DROPPED! Ajaz Patel bowls this slightly short and outside off, at a quicker pace. Naseem Shah gets forward and pushes at the ball but it hits him high on the bat. The ball goes in the air to the right of silly point where Tom Latham is placed. He sticks his right hand out and gets to the ball but is unable to hold on. It was a difficult chance but another opportunity goes begging.
Daryl Mitchell starts with the outside off stump line on a good length. Left alone.

Bowls this on a good length and angles this into the stumps. Saud Shakeel looks to clip this towards the leg side but misses. Gets hit on the pads and there is an appeal but this is going down leg side.
Bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Rises sharply after bouncing and Saud Shakeel keeps his arms down to let the ball through.
Goes slightly fuller this time but still wide outside off. Saud Shakeel raises his bat and lets it through to the keeper.
On a good length this time and still outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel shoulders his arms to this one.
Goes full and in line with the stumps. Saud Shakeel flicks this towards mid-wicket.

Ish Sodhi bowls a googly full and outside the off stump. Naseem Shah looks to punch this away but it stays low and Naseem Shah gets a slight inside edge. The ball goes into the keeper's hands and the umpire goes upstairs to check for a catch. The soft signal is not out and replays confirm it bounces before the keeper's gloves.
FOUR! This has been hoicked away! Ish Sodhi bowls another googly short and into the stumps. Naseem Shah lofts this towards wide long on for four runs.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Naseem Shah blocks this to the off side.

OUT! TIMBER! Ish Sodhi gets his first wicket and Pakistan are crumbling here! Ish Sodhi serves a googly on a shorter length and gets it to come back into the stumps from outside off. Naseem Shah make room to play this through the off side but misses the ball and watches his stumps get shattered. Pakistan lose their eighth wicket and after controlling the entire day find themselves once again on the back foot. New Zealand will now be looking to wrap up the tail before stumps.
Howout: b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: OUT! BOWLED! Ish Sodhi is on a HAT-TRICK and New Zealand have dug deep to wrench the advantage back in their favor. Ish Sodhi flights this one full and outside the off pole. Mir Hamza takes a long stride forward and looks to defend this but leaves a gap between bat and pad. The ball turns sharply after pitching and creeps into the gap to peg back the stumps. The New Zealand players are ecstatic as they have had very little to cheer all day but they will be delighted by the fact that they still have the advantage in this game. Just one wicket more to put an end to Pakistan's inning and it will be Abrar Ahmed who makes his way out to the crease.
Howout: b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: This is slightly short and in line with the stumps. Abrar Ahmed manages to keep this one out.
Fires this one wide outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel leaves this alone.
Bowls this full and in line with stumps. Saud Shakeel defends this back down the pitch.
Continues bowling full and outside off. Saud Shakeel defends this towards cover.
Full once again and outside the off stump. Saud Shakeel happy to block this away.
FOUR! Stand and deliver! Ajaz Patel floats this one full and outside off. Saud Shakeel lofts this towards long off for four runs.
FOUR! Two boundaries in a row! Ajaz Patel bowls this short and outside off. Saud Shakeel pulls this towards deep mid-wicket for four more runs.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off. Abrar Ahmed knocks this towards cover.
This is full as well and wide outside off. Abrar Ahmed cuts this to the right of slip who stops it well.
Bowls a flipper this time but fires this down leg side. Abrar Ahmed leaves this one alone.
NO BALL! A high full toss, it slips off his hands. No ball for height.
Pushed through quicker, wide of off. Ahmed looks to chase it but misses.
This one turns in from outside off. Ahmed goes back and nudges it to short leg.
Gives it a lot of air this time. Full and wide outside off. Ahmed dabs it out.
Fuller, outside off. Shakeel dabs it to slip.
Outside off, blocked out on the front foot.
Flatter, outside off. Shakeel plays it late to point.
Fuller, just outside off. Shakeel goes back and smothers it out.
A single now as this is swept to square leg. Abrar Ahmed needs to survive one delivery before stumps.
This is full, coming in with the arm, Abrar Ahmed prods and blocks it to the leg side. So, Abrar Ahmed does defend the final delivery solidly and THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3.
Floats it up, wide of off. It grips and turns in. Shakeel defends it back to the bowler.
Sarfaraz Ahmed tries to sweep but misses.
On middle and leg, nudged to mid-wicket.
Saud Shakeel goes back and works it to the leg side.
Flatter one, on off. Saud Shakeel rocks back and hit it down to long on. They take one.

OUT! LBW! So, Ish Sodhi gets the final wicket here. Abrar Ahmed takes the review instantly. It is tossed up, around off, turns in a touch. Abrar Ahmed tries to defend it out but misses. He gets rapped on his pads. It looks plumb and the umpire raises his finger. The review also does not save the batter here as the Ball Tracking confirms three reds.
Howout: lbw b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: WIDE! Starts with a loosener. Good length, angled across the left-hander, wide of off. Tom Latham leaves it alone. Wide called.
Much better from Shah. This is full, closer to the batter. Latham is forced to play a defensive shot here.
Tom Latham shuffles and tucks this good-length ball from outside off towards mid-wicket.
Length and on off, blocked away.
FOUR! EDGY! It is a full-length ball, around off. Tom Latham gets it past gullly off the outside edge. It races away to the fence.
Outside off, left alone.
It is a length ball, in the channel. Tom Latham lets it be.

OUT! TIMBER! Mir Hamza strikes instantly and gets rid of Devon Conway early on. Just what the doctor ordered for the hosts. Devon Conway walks back on a golden deck. It is a length ball, that lands just outside off and nips in off the deck. Devon Conway tries to defend it out on his front foot but ends up playing the wrong line. The ball zips past the inside edge and shatters the stumps.
Howout: b Mir Hamza

Commentary: This one goes across the right-hander. It stays low off the deck. Kane Williamson tries to go after it but misses.
Length and on leg, nudged to the leg side.
A length ball, down leg. Kane Williamson nudges it to deep square leg and crosses.
Outside off, left alone.
This is a length ball, on off. Tom Latham blocks it out solidly.
Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson gets his bat out of the way and leaves this one alone.
Continues bowling on a good length and just outside off. Kane Williamson pushes this towards mid on.

This is on a good length as well and nips back in sharply. Kane Williamson looks to block but misses and gets hit on the pad. Huge appeal from the bowler but Babar Azam feels there are two noises and does not review this. Replays confirm there is an inside edge.
Angles this into the pads on a good length. Kane Williamson misses his flick and the ball goes to square leg off his pads. They take a leg bye.

FOUR! Second boundary of the innings from Tom Latham and this one looks convincing! Naseem Shah bowls this a touch fuller and outside the off stump. Tom Latham punches this straight towards long off for four runs.
FOUR LEG BYES! Bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Tom Latham gets squared up the ball goes off his thigh pads past the slip cordon towards third man for four leg byes.
Mir Hamza angles this away from the batter from outside off and on a good length. Kane Williamson is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
Gets this one to come back in a bit from a good length and just outside off. Kane Williamson blocks this solidly back down the pitch.

FOUR BYES! This is on a good length as well and outside the off stump. The ball stays really low and goes on the bounce to the keeper as Kane Williamson leaves it alone. Sarfaraz Ahmed is unable to hold on and the ball goes behind him for four byes.
Goes a touch fuller this time and outside the off pole. Kane Williamson defends this towards short cover.
Continues bowling just outside the off stump on a fraction fuller length. Kane Williamson is looking solid in defense as he plays this to the short cover fielder.
Bowls this one slightly wider outside off on a good length. Kane Williamson shoulders his arms to this one.
Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Tom Latham leaves this one well and there is good carry on the ball as it goes through to the keeper.
Goes fuller this time and in line with the stumps. Tom Latham blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues to attack the stumps and this is bowled on a good length. Tom Latham flicks this towards mid-wicket.
Slightly fuller this time and on an outside off stump line. Tom Latham is watchful and leave it alone.
This is bowled on a good length and outside the off pole. Tom Latham defends this back into the pitch.
Offers width outside off and bowls this on a good length. Tom Latham raises his arms and the ball goes through to Sarfaraz Ahmed behind the wicket.
Mir Hamza bowls this full and just outside off. Kane Williamson gets his bat down and blocks this out towards cover.
Continues bowling full and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson taps this towards the gully fielder.
An absolute beauty! Bowls this in line with the stumps and gets it to angle away from the batter. Kane Williamson plays the wrong line and gets beaten all ends up.

FOUR! A lucky boundary and Mir Hamza is causing some problems here! Another delivery angling away from the right-hander bowled just outside off on a fuller length. Kane Williamson pushes at this and gets a thick outside edge to fly past the slip fielders for four runs to third man.
Bowls this on a good length but strays down leg. Kane Williamson tucks this to deep backward square leg and gets off strike with a single.
Delivers this one full and angled into the left-hander from outside off. Tom Latham blocks this solidly towards point.
Naseem Shah bowls this full and into the stumps. Kane Williamson defends this back towards the bowler.
Pulls his length back a fraction and serves this outside off. Kane Williamson is happy to leave this one alone.
Angles this into the pads on a fuller length. Kane Williamson clips this towards mid-wicket.
On a fuller length still but this is outside the off stump. Kane Williamson smothers this into the pitch at his feet.
Continues bowling full and on an outside off stump line. Kane Williamson dabs this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
This one is on a good length and outside the off pole. Kane Williamson defends this towards cover.
Mir Hamza bowls this a touch full and outside off. Tom Latham gets his front foot forward and strokes this towards deep cover-point for a couple of runs.
Angles this into the pads on a fuller length. Tom Latham flicks this to the left of mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Bowls this full as well and just outside off. Kane Williamson blocks this into the off side and raises his arms in despair as there is some issue with the sightscreen once again.
On a fuller length once again and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson gets his front foot forward and defends this solidly towards cover.
Continues bowling full and outside off, very little movement off the pitch this over. Kane Williamson knocks this towards mid off.
Bowls this on a good length this time and outside the off pole. Kane Williamson is well behind the line of the ball as he dabs this towards the short cover fielder.
Naseem Shah serves this on a good length and outside the off stump. Tom Latham judges the line of the ball and leaves this one alone.
This is on a good length as well and closer to the off pole. Tom Latham defends this towards point.
Goes full this time and on an off stump line. Tom Latham pushes this towards mid on.

FOUR! That has been timed to perfection! Naseem Shah bowls this back of a length and offers width outside off. Tom Latham gets on top of the bounce and cuts this towards deep cover-point for four runs.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump. Tom Latham knocks this to the right of mid off and takes a single as Babar Azam dives to his right to stop the ball.
Strays onto the pads on a fuller length. Kane Williamson clips this down to fine leg and takes one to retain strike.

Abrar Ahmed starts off with a full delivery angling down leg. Kane Williamson looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal from the bowler but the umpire remains unmoved. Babar Azam takes his time and eventually opts for the review. UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows that the ball is pitching in line but the impact is outside leg. Pakistan lose a review and Kane Williamson survives.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson gets well forward and defends this into the off side.
Flights this one and bowls this in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Kane Williamson smothers this into the pitch.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Kane Williamson uses his feet well as he gets a stride forward and defends this towards the bowler.
This is just outside the off stump on a fuller length. Kane Williamson dabs this down towards short leg.
Bowls this one slightly short and just outside the off pole. Kane Williamson goes deep in the crease and defends this solidly. A maiden to start off from Abrar Ahmed.
Hasan Ali begins from 'round the wicket to the left-hander and serves this on a good length, just outside off. Tom Latham gets across the stumps and defends this into the leg side.
Bowls this slightly fuller and outside the off stump. Tom Latham blocks this solidly towards cover.
This is on a good length but still outside the off pole. Tom Latham looks comfortable as he dabs this towards the cover fielder.
Angles this into the pads on a good length. Tom Latham tucks this away towards deep square leg and they pick up a couple of runs.
Goes over the wicket now and serves this full, outside off. Tom Latham defends this well towards cover.
Strays way down leg side on a fuller length. Tom Latham looks to flick this away but misses as the ball goes through to the keeper.
Abrar Ahmed floats this one full and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson plays this late towards third man and picks up and couple of runs.

Flights this one really full and coming into the pads. Kane Williamson looks to flick this leg side but plays all over the ball and gets hit on the pads. Another huge appeal from the bowler and this time he has support from the wicket-keeper and the slip fielder. Babar Azam enquires and he obliges them by going upstairs. UltraEdge shows that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates the ball is missing the leg stump. Pakistan have just one review remaining now.
Loops this full and in line with the stumps. Kane Williamson smothers this into the pitch.
FOUR! Kane Williamson uses his feet well here! Abrar Ahmed flights this one full and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson charges down the wicket and thumps this towards long on for four runs.
Goes full once again and wider outside off. Kane Williamson knocks this towards cover-point and takes a single.
Bowls this one full and on a leg stumps line. Tom Latham gets his front foot away from the line of the ball and defends this back towards the bowler.
Ali goes full and just outside off. Kane Williamson leans in and drives it into covers.
Very full, wide of off. swinging in late. Williamson strokes it to point off the front foot.
On a length, outside off. Kane Williamson punches it through the line towards cover.
Good length, on top of off. Kane Williamson goes back and defends it to mid off.
Length, outside off, nips back in late. Kane Williamson makes a solid leave.
Kane Williamson hits this full ball straight to the fielder at covers. A maiden now for Ali.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. Latham blocks it on his front foot.
Fuller, outside off. Tom Latham drives it to cover and scampers across for a quick single.
Ahmed goes full, attacking the stumps. Kane Williamson gets forward and dabs it into the deck.
Kane Williamson sweeps it down to fine leg and crosses.
Fuller, just outside off. Latham eases it back to the bowler.
Loops it up, full and outside off. Tom Latham gets low and sweeps it to backward square leg.
A length ball, tailing back in from outside off. Kane Williamson blocks it with a straight bat.
Gos full this time, attacking the stumps. Kane Williamson digs it out.
Three dots on the trot. Full again, on off. Kane Williamson defends it back to the bowler on his front foot.
Just short of a length ball, around off, it nips back in a bit. Kane Williamson blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off, shaping in late. Kane Williamson lets it be.

FOUR! Exceptional shot! Almost carries to Babar Azam at backward point. A good-length ball, wide of off. It spits off the deck. Kane Williamson rocks back and cuts it past backward point, where Azam dives to his right but only manages to get fingertips on it. The ball races away.
On off, blocked.
Tosses it up, wide of off. Latham prods and blocks it into covers.
This full ball is swept to the man at square leg.
Gives it a little more air, on off. Tom Latham pushes it to the right of the bowler.
BEATEN! This is a loopy ball, coming in with the arm, outside off. Tom Latham tries to block it on his front foot. The ball grips and turns away sharply. Tom Latham gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, defended out.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kane Williamson squares up and eases it back to the bowler.
Another dot now! A length ball, in the channel, dabbed down to gully.
FOUR! Short and punished. Back of a length, around off. It flies off the deck. Kane Williamson rides the bounce and pulls it in front of square on the leg side. It goes for four.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Kane Williamson tucks it to square leg.
An inswinger now, full and on off. Kane Williamson shuffles and taps it back to the bowler.
Just short of full length, in the channel. Kane Williamson defends it out watchfully. The Kiwis lead by 93 runs now.
It is tossed up, full and outside off. Tom Latham brings out the reverse sweep. The ball deflects to fine leg off the slip fielder. They cross.
On off, defended to covers.
This is pushed through quicker, on off. Kane Williamson goes back and blocks it.
Fuller, on leg, defended to short leg.
BEATEN! It is tossed up, wide of off. Kane Williamson tries to poke at it but gets beaten by the turn this time.
On the pads, nudged towards mid on.
FOUR! Agha Salman has been welcomed with a boundary! He serves this short and outside off, Tom Latham shifts his weight onto the back foot and hoicks this towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Floated full and in line with the stumps. Tom Latham defends this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
FOUR! The second boundary of the over! Agha Salman bowls a low full toss angling down leg. Tom Latham sweeps this towards deep backward square leg and collects four more runs.
On off, blocked.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Touch short, outside off. Latham punches it to point off the back foot. Not in the gap though. 8 runs come off it. New Zealand are planning to take on the new bowler here.
Outside off, Kane Williamson prods and defends.
Kane Williamson flicks it off his pads to deep square leg. They cross.
Floats it up, full and on off. Latham blocks it into the deck.
FOUR! Into the gap! This is very full, outside off. Tom Latham leans in and creams it through covers for four runs.
Quite short, outside off. Tom Latham tries to cut it away but gets an inside edge on it.
Loops it up, on off, defended out watchfully.
Dated on the pads, Kane Williamson gets inside and clips is past short leg for a single.
Short ball, outside off. Latham chops it to covers.
On off, Latham smothers it on his front foot.
Loops it up, just outside off. Latham prods and blocks.
It is outside off, left alone by Latham.
Fuller, outside off. Latham blocks it on his front foot.
On the stumps, blocked back to the bowler.
A single now as this is knocked down to long on.
FOUR! A wonderful sweep shot from Latham. It is fuller, wide of off. Tom Latham gets down on one knee and sweeps it through square leg for four runs.
Pushed through quicker and on off. Latham uses his feet and blocks it back to the bowler.
On off, defended.

Abrar Ahmed makes a loud appeal, a long one. The umpire gives it a thought and raises the finger. Let's talk about the delivery here - It is tossed up, full and around off, which comes in with the arm. Tom Latham prods and looks to block it away but misses. He gets pinged on his pads. The umpire gives it out. Although the review is taken and the Ball Tracking confirms that the impact is outside the line. The umpire has to overturn his decision here.
Loops it up, on off, defended out.
Around off, nudged to short leg.
Fuller, just outside off, blocked out.
A single now as this is clipped to mid on.
Agha Salman bowls this slightly short and just outside off. Tom Latham goes on the back foot and knocks this back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads on a fuller length. Tom Latham clips this towards square leg.
Floated and full, down leg. Kane Williamson gets low and sweeps it down to fine leg for a single.
Goes full and on off. Latham sweeps it to deep square leg for one.
On off, blocked.
This is full, spilled down leg. Kane Williamson goes for the sweep but gets it to fine leg off the top edge. They take a single.
On off, defended out.
Much flatter, on off pole. Tom Latham goes back and blocks.
This is tossed up, outside off. Kane Williamson looks to chase it but misses.
On off, Williamson prods and blocks it to short leg.
Fuller, on leg, defended out.
Goes full and on off. Kane Williamson uses his feet and clips it to the leg side.
Full again, into the pads. Kane Williamson works it to mid on.
Full, outside off. Blocked out on the front foot. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4.
Abrar Ahmed starts off with a full delivery outside off. Tom Latham goes back in the crease and taps it into the off side.
This is angled into the pads on a fuller length. Tom Latham clips this towards square leg.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Tom Latham sweeps this straight to short third man.
Strays onto the pads this time on a fuller length. Tom Latham glances this to the left of the short third man fielder and takes a single.
Loops this full and in line with the stumps. Kane Williamson blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
This one is a fraction short and spinning into the batter from outside off. Kane Williamson dabs it down at the short leg fielder.

Mir Hamza begins this spell with a good length delivery in line with the stumps. Tom Latham punches this back past the bowler and they take a single as the fielder at mid off comes across to cut it off.
Beaten! Mir Hamza gets this on a good length and the ball keeps its line angling away from off stump. Kane Williamson feels for the ball and is unable to connect.

FOUR! Kane Williamson slaps this away and it looks so easy for him! Mir Hamza bowls this slightly short but offers ample width outside off. Kane Williamson gets across the stumps and cuts this towards deep point for four runs.

Kane Williamson timing the ball beautifully here! This is bowled fuller and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson gets his front foot forward and strokes this firmly but straight to the cover fielder.
Mir Hamza goes 'round the wicket now and bowls this full and coming in from outside off. Kane Williamson blocks this into the leg side.
Delivers this one on a good length but wide outside off. Kane Williamson is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
Abrar Ahmed flights this one full and outside the off stump. Tom Latham taps this towards point.
A full toss this time angled into the stumps. Tom Latham misses out as he prepared for the sweep and in the end slaps it away towards square leg for a single.
Bowls this one full and outside off. Kane Williamson taps this towards mid on with soft hands and takes a quick single.
Tosses this on full and just outside off. Tom Latham uses his wrists and clips this to the right of short leg.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Tom Latham sweeps this straight to backward square leg.
Angles this one down leg side on a fuller length. Tom Latham glances this to the short third man fielder.
Mir Hamza begins the over from 'round the wicket and bowls this slightly full, outside off. Kane Williamson shoulders his arms to this one.
Bowls this on a good length and angled in from well outside off. Kane Williamson gets behind the line of the ball and defends it back down the pitch.

NO BALL! Goes really full this time and wide outside off. Kane Williamson guides this towards deep backward point and they have to settle for a single. Mir Hamza has overstepped though and it has been called a no ball.
Goes over the wicket to the southpaw and serves this on a good length, on an off stump line. Tom Latham defends this back towards the bowler.
Strays onto the pads this time on a good length. Tom Latham flicks this down to third man and takes an easy single.
This is on a good length as well and angling away from the batter. Kane Williamson taps this to the left of cover with soft hands and takes a quick single.

FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Mir Hamza bowls this full and just outside the off stump. Tom Latham gets into position and plays a beautiful cover drive in the gap between cover and mid off for four runs. He is one hit away from a half-century.
Abrar Ahmed flights this full and outside off. Kane Williamson shimmies down the wicket and defends this back down the pitch.
Bowls this one short and outside off. Kane Williamson cuts this towards deep point for a single.
Angles this one down leg on a fuller length. Tom Latham misses his sweep and gets hit on the pads.

DROPPED! Difficult opportunity but a chance nonetheless! Abrar Ahmed bowls this slightly short and angles this into the stumps. Tom Latham looks to flick this off the back foot but hits it in the air. Babar Azam makes a valiant effort diving to his left and gets a hand on it. He is unable to hold on though and they take two runs.
Flights this full and in line with the stump. Tom Latham takes a good stride forward and defends this back down the pitch.
Angles this onto the pads on a fuller length. Tom Latham clips this to the right of short third man and takes one.
Naseem Shah begins with a good length delivery outside off. Tom Latham looks to push this into the offside but inside edge it towards mid on.

FOUR! That is FIFTY for Tom Latham as he continues to accumulate runs! Bowls this one slightly full and outside off. Tom Latham plays at it with soft hands and pierces the gap in the slip cordon for four runs to third man.
This is on a good length and just outside off. Tom Latham blocks this solidly towards cover.
Continues bowling on a good length and a shade wider this time outside off. Tom Latham is happy to leave this one alone.
Bowls this one on an off stump line and on a good length. Tom Latham defends this with a steady head towards mid off.
Goes a fraction fuller and outside the off pole. Tom Latham continues to be defensive as he dabs this towards cover.

FOUR! A beautiful stroke from Kane Williamson and this is all about the wristwork! Abrar Ahmed bowls this slightly short and into the pads. Kane Williamson whips it towards deep mid-wicket for four runs.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson defends this back down the pitch.
Another loopy delivery, this time in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Kane Williamson blocks this back towards the bowler.
Continues to float this full and just outside the off pole. Kane Williamson smothers this into the pitch.
Slightly short this time and outside the off stump. Kane Williamson rocks back and punches this straight to extra cover.
A loopy delivery tossed up full and outside off. Kane Williamson goes back to defending on the front foot.
Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length and on a leg stump line. Tom Latham clips this towards mid-wicket.
Continues bowling on a good length and this time just outside off. Tom Latham blocks this solidly towards cover.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a good length. Tom Latham knocks this with a straight bat towards mid off.
Attacks the stumps once again and continues to bowl on a good length. Tom Latham pats this back towards the bowler.

EDGED AND FOUR! Naseem Shah has been really good but is really unlucky here! He bowls this on a good length and slightly wider outside the off pole. Tom Latham goes for the expansive drive and gets a thick outside edge that flies in the gap at slips for a boundary to third man.
This is on a good length as well and outside the off stump. Tom Latham taps this towards cover and takes a quick single to retain strike.
Fires this one full and angling down leg. Tom Latham looks to sweep this away but misses and Sarfaraz Ahmed does well behind the wicket.

This is a fraction short and pitching in line with the stumps. Tom Latham looks to tuck this into the leg side but misses. The bowler is convinced that this is leg before the wicket and there is a huge appeal. The umpire says it is not out and Babar Azam does not review this. Replays show that Tom Latham would have been a goner had they gone upstairs.
Bowls this full and outside the off stump. Tom Latham defends this on his back foot into the off side.
This is floated full and outside off. Tom Latham whips this towards mid-wicket.
This is slightly short and spinning into the pads. Tom Latham clips this towards square leg for a single.
Fuller, on leg. Defended with full face. Just a single off the over. Abrar Ahmed even could've had a wicket to his name, if Azam would've taken the review.
FOUR! Exceptional shot! This is full and on middle. Tom Latham drills it down the track and finds the boundary.
This is on a good length and in line with the stumps. Tom Latham defends this towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT Pakistan have the breakthrough and it is a brilliant catch from Abrar Ahmed that ends the 109-run stand! Naseem Shah bowls this on a fuller length and on a leg stump line. Tom Latham looks to flick this away but hits it uppishly to the left of square leg. Abrar Ahmed dives to his left and takes a one-handed catch in mid-air. He gets up and takes off in celebration as he is also stunned by his effort. New Zealand lose their second wicket and a dangerous Tom Latham has to make the long walk back to the shed.
Howout: c Abrar Ahmed b Naseem Shah

Commentary: This is bowled full and in line with the stump. Henry Nicholls blocks this towards cover.

Naseem Shah bowls this on a good length and outside the off pole. Henry Nicholls pushes at the ball and there is some noise as it passes the bat. Sarfaraz Ahmed pouches the ball diving ahead and all the Pakistan players are already celebrating. The umpire raises his finger and Henry Nicholls reviews this straight away. Replays show that there is a significant gap between the bat and the ball with UltraEdge confirming the same. The umpire has to reverse his decision as it is NOT OUT.
A dot to end a successful over! It is a length ball, angled acoss, ouside off. Henry Nicholls presses forward and blocks it out.
On leg, tucked to short leg.
Flatter, just outside off. Kane Williamson knocks it to cover-point.

OUT! LBW! This looks plumb and the umpire raises his finger in a flash. Kane Williamson though takes the review. Coming to the delivery. It is tossed up, full and on middle. It dips onto the batter. Kane Williamson prods and tries to sweep it away but misses. The ball rolls under his blade and raps him on his pads. Kane Williamson do not lose a review as it is umpire's call on the ball hitting the wickets. Although, the Kiwis lose another set batter here. Pakistan are making a solid comeback.
Howout: lbw b Abrar Ahmed

Commentary: Once again Abrar Ahmed puts in an appeal and the umpire raises his finger without any hesitation. Tom Blundell thinks he is safe and takes the review. It is a loopy ball, around middle, turning in a hint. Tom Blundell gets beaten on the inside edge and gets pinged on his pads. The UltraEdge later confirms that there is bat on it. Even Tom Blundell didn't feel that he nicked it but he surely would be glad about it.
Tom Blundell now gets off the mark, as this full ball is clipped behind square on the leg side.
Full, on middle. Defended. A wicket-taking over from Ahmed comes to an end.
A length ball, around off, defended out watchfully.
This is full, just outside off, shaping away a touch. Tom Blundell blocks it out on his front foot.
Shah dishes a length ball, wide of off, shaping further away from the batter. Left alone.
Length ball, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell fends it towards gully.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell pushes this towards mid off.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell knocks this towards the cover fielder.
Flatter and on off. Henry Nicholls nudges it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Henry Nicholls comes forward and works it to mid on.
Gives it a lot of air this time, around middle. Henry Nicholls tries to block it on his front foot but gets it off the inside edge past short leg.
Short and on off. Defended.
Tosses it up, full and outside off. Henry Nicholls smothers it on his front foot.
Angling across, full and outside off. Henry Nicholls fends it out to covers.
A tight leave! It is a length ball, that lands outside off that nips back in a long way. Tom Blundell prods but shoulders his arms at it.
Length, outside off, blocked to point.
Tom Blundell defends this length ball on his front foot.
On a length, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell prods and defends it to gully.
Full, on middle and leg, Tom Blundell works it to mid on.
FOUR! Easy pickings! It is a full-length ball, sliding down leg. Tom Blundell stays back and flicks it through square leg for four runs. A much-needed boundary!
Looped up, outside off. Henry Nicholls taps it to the right of the bowler.
Around off, defended.
Full, on leg, coming in with the arm. Henry Nicholls nudges it to mid-wicket.
Henry Nicholls prods and blocks it out solidly.
This is spilled down leg. Henry Nicholls tucks it to short fine leg.
Henry Nicholls uses his feet and tucks it to mid-wicket. A maiden for Abrar Ahmed now. New Zealand are under pressure now.
FOUR! Hasan Ali has been treated to a boundary straight up! He bowls this wide outside off on a length. Tom Blundell waits on the ball and cuts this towards deep backward point for four runs.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell makes an exaggerated leave getting his front foot forward.
Continues bowling on a good length and this is closer to the off pole. Tom Blundell looks to block but inside edge it back into the pitch.
Goes full this time and angles this into the stumps. Tom Blundell knocks this straight to mid on.
Delivers this full once again and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell pushes at the ball but it nips back in slightly and gets an inside edge towards square leg.
This is slightly short and outside off. Tom Blundell cuts this straight to point.
Abrar Ahmed floats this full and outside off. Henry Nicholls knocks this to deep cover and takes a easy single.
Tosses this one full and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell clips this to short leg.
Bowls this slightly short and just outside off. Tom Blundell rocks back and punches this to cover.
Loopy delivery bowled full and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell blocks this back down the pitch.
Another floated delivery served full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell defends this back towards the bowler.
Continues to bowl full and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell is watchful as he taps this into the offside.

FOUR! Edgy boundary once again! Hasan Ali goes 'round the wicket and serves this full and outside off. Henry Nicholls plays for the ball and gets a thick edge that falls just short of the second slip fielder and bounces past him for a boundary to third man.
This is on a good length and just outside the off pole. Henry Nicholls is well behind this one as he knocks this towards point.
Continues to bowl on a good length and wide outside off. Henry Nicholls works this to the right of backward point and they decide not to take a run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Hasan Ali gets a wicket and New Zealand are losing the plot here! Hasan Ali bangs this in short and outside off. Henry Nicholls looks to pull this away to the leg side but the ball hits him high on the bat and loops up towards mid off. Babar Azam takes a comfortable catch and Pakistan have their fourth wicket. They are clawing themselves back into the game and New Zealand have some work to do here if they are to stay alive in this game. The lead is 169 at the moment.
Howout: c Babar Azam b Hasan Ali

Commentary: Fires a yorker full and into the stumps from ‘round the wicket. Michael Bracewell manages to dig this out back towards the bowler.
This is full as well and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell pushes at this and gets an outside edge just short of third slip.
Abrar Ahmed bowls a flighted delivery full and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell defends this back down the pitch.
This is short and wide outside off. Tom Blundell cuts this towards deep point for a single.
A loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell edges this past slip for a single.
Fires this one full and into the stumps. Tom Blundell clips this towards square leg for a run.

Abrar Ahmed bowls this slightly short and just outside off. gets the ball to spin back into the left-hander. Michael Bracewell misses the ball and gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal one again but the umpire remains unmoved. Babar Azam does not review this once again.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell knocks this straight to mid off.
Hasan Ali bowls this full and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell strokes this straight to cover.
This is full as well and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell punches this towards mid on.
Nails the yorker this time and aims for the stumps. Tom Blundell gets his bat down in time and digs this out towards the bowler.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell looks to block but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Goes full this time and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell gets a confident stride forward and caresses this towards deep cover for three runs.
Bowls this one on a length and angling away from the batter. Michael Bracewell initially looks to play at it but decides to leave it alone in the end.
Around middle, this stays low. Blundell punches it to the off side.
On off, blocked into the deck.
This is full and on off, Tom Blundell whips it past mid on for two runs.
It is full, on the stumps. Tom Blundell gets it past short leg off the inside edge. They take a single.
BEATEN! This is angled across the left-hander. Getting some extra bounce. Michael Bracewell gets beaten on the outside edge.
Incredible bowling! Michael Bracewell gets beaten again. It is fuller, angling away from the left-hander with some extra bounce once again. Michael Bracewell is unable to deal with it.
It is a short ball, outside off. Tom Blundell looks to chase it but misses.
Full length, wide outside off. Tom Blundell drives it to deep point for a single.
Some reverse swing now, which carries to the keeper. Michael Bracewell shuffles and tries to block it inside the line.
Length ball, angled across. Michael Bracewell presses forward and gets it to the off side off the outer half.
A length ball, outside off. This one dies as it reaches the keeper. Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.
Ali comes 'round the wicket for his final delivery and serves it on a length, outside off. It straightens a bit. Michael Bracewell blocks it on his front foot.
Abrar Ahmed floats this one full and outside off. Tom Blundell goes on the back foot and pushes this away towards cover.
Flights this one full as well and outside off. Tom Blundell dabs this towards point.
Slightly short this time and outside off. Tom Blundell transfers his weight back and knocks this toward cover.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell defends this back down the pitch.
Angled into the pads on a fuller length. Tom Blundell taps this down to short leg.
Goes full once again and straight. Tom Blundell flicks this to deep backward square leg for a single and will keep strike.
Hasan Ali bowls a short ball and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell gets across the stumps and pulls this towards deep square leg for a single.
This is on a good length and just outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell defends this solidly towards cover.
Bowls this one on a fuller length and angling away from the left-hander. Michael Bracewell looks to defend but gets an outside edge that bounces short of the second slip fielder.
On a good length this time and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell gets squared up and the ball goes off the outside part of the bat to fall just short of gully.
Goes full this time and in line with the stumps. Michael Bracewell flicks this towards mid on.
Bowls 'round the wicket this time and bowls this full, angled into the stumps. Michael Bracewell defends this firmly back towards the bowler.

Abrar Ahmed bowls this really slow in the air but it is short and wide. Tom Blundell has all the time to punch this for four but find the cover fielder. Some misunderstanding between the batters but they get across for a single.
This is slightly short and outside off. Michael Bracewell tucks this into the leg side.
FOUR! Lovely use of the feet! Abrar Ahmed floats this one full and on a leg stump line. Michael Bracewell shimmies down the wicket and knocks this towards long off along the turf for four runs.
A fraction short once again and outside off. Michael Bracewell punches this off the back foot towards cover and they take a single from a misfield.
Bowls this short as well and spins into the stumps from outside off. Tom Blundell dabs this down to short leg.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell defends this into the offside.
Hasan Ali bowls this on a fuller length but well outside the off stump from 'round the wicket. Michael Bracewell chooses to leave this one alone.
On a good length this time and just outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell looks to defend but gets an outside edge that bounces behind towards the keeper.
Goes full this time but still outside off. Michael Bracewell gets a stride forward and blocks this towards cover.

Continues bowling full and angling down leg. Michael Bracewell looks to flick this but plays all over the ball. Gets hit on the pads and there is a huge appeal from the bowler. He knows this is going down leg and walks back to his mark. There is a massive inside edge as well.
This is full as well and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell dabs this towards the point fielder.

FOUR! Michael Bracewell is living in danger here! He persists with the outside off stump line on a fuller length and manages to induce an edge as Michael Bracewell pushes at the ball. The ball flies through the packed slip cordon for four runs to third man.

Loopy delivery bowled full and wide outside the off stump. Tom Blundell looks to play at it but misses. Abrar Ahmed is convinced this has taken the edge and tries to convince his captain. Babar Azam refuses to take the review though.
Bowls this full and just outside off. Tom Blundell dabs this towards short leg.

Continues to float this full and outside off. Tom Blundell feels for this and gets an edge that takes the ball away from the keeper's gloves. Sarfaraz Ahmed could have done better though and a chance goes begging.
Abrar Ahmed gives the ball air and bowls this outside the off stump on a fuller length. Tom Blundell eases this down to long off for a single.
Tosses this one full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell defends this towards point.
Another flighted delivery bowled on a fuller length and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell knocks this towards cover.
Mir Hamza starts off with a good-length delivery on a leg stump line. Tom Blundell clips this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this one on a good length as well and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell defends this back down the pitch.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell taps this towards point and takes a quick single.

On a good length this time and just outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell looks to block and gets a bottom edge into the pitch at his feet. The ball is bouncing onto the stumps but Michael Bracewell is well aware and manages to kick the ball away.
Bowls this in line with the stumps and on a good length. Michael Bracewell punches this towards mid on.
Fires this one full and into the pads. Michael Bracewell flicks the ball towards dep square leg for a single and will retain strike.
FOUR! Michael Bracewell manages to get this fine! Abrar Ahmed bowls this full and angling down leg. Michael Bracewell glances this past leg slip for four runs to fine leg.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell dabs this into the off side.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell attempts the sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. Another huge appeal turned down by the umpire.
This is slightly short and just outside off. Michael Bracewell gets squared up by the turn and gets hit on the back pad.
FOUR! Great use of the wrists here! Abrar Ahmed goes full and on the pads. Michael Bracewell whips this towards deep square leg and collects four runs.
This is short and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell looks to defend on the back foot but gets beaten.

FOUR! Free runs for New Zealand here! Mir Hamza strays down leg side and serves this on a length. Tom Blundell gets a bit of bat on that as he looks to clip this away and the ball goes past the diving keeper for four runs.
This is on a good length and just outside the off stump. Tom Blundell blocks this towards the mid off fielder.
Goes 'round the wicket now and bowls this outside off on a fuller length. Tom Blundell gets his front foot forward and leaves the ball alone.
Slower delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell is early into his shot as he looks to push this away and gets beaten. The ball goes on the bounce to Sarfaraz Ahmed.
On a fuller length once again and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell taps this towards the point fielder.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell gets on his toes and looks to work it leg side but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
This is spilled down leg, Michael Bracewell flicks it behind square on the leg side for one.
Fraction short, outside off, punched towards point.
On off, blocked out.
Pushed through full and on off. Tom Blundell defends it on his front foot.
This full ball is driven down the ground for a single.
Darted on the pads, Michael Bracewell tries to glance it around the corner but does not get any bat on it. The ball goes to fine leg off the pads. They collect a leg bye.
Good length, wide of off. It climbs on the batter. Michael Bracewell lets it be.
Once again wide outside off. Michael Bracewell shuffles and leaves it alone.
It is much fuller, on off. Michael Bracewell blocks it to the leg side off the inside edge.
Another dot now! This is full, angling away from the left-hander. Michael Bracewell watches it sail past him.
On a length, jags back in from outside off. Michael Bracewell blocks it out solidly.
On a length, on fourth stump. Michael Bracewell gets across and defends it with an angled bat. A maiden for Mir Hamza this time.
Fuller, on the pads. Tom Blundell prods and defends off the inner half.
A short ball that stays low off the deck. Tom Blundell slaps it back to the bowler off the toe-end.
On off, defended on the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is tossed up, on off. Tom Blundell comes down the track and lifts it over mid on. A couple of bounces and into the ropes.
Pushed through, on middle and leg. Blundell tucks it to the leg side.

DROPPED! This one is looped up, around off, Tom Blundell gets a thickish outside edge on it. The ball carries to Agha Salman at first slip who makes a mess of it. The take a single as it rolls to fine leg.
Goes full, on middle and leg. Tom Blundell whips it to square leg for two runs.
Length and on off, blocked.
Hamza serves a length ball, around leg. Tom Blundell flicks it to square leg off his pads for two runs this time.
Fuller, outside off. Blundell dabs it to point.

FOUR! EDGED but through the gap it goes! It is a full-length ball, shaping away. Tom Blundell gets a thick outside edge as he goes for the booming drive. It flies past gully and races away to the third man fence. Mir Hamza is gutted.
Length and on off, defended out solidly. New Zealand lead by 222 runs now.
Flatter, on off. Michael Bracewell tucks it to the leg side.
Flicked off the pads through mid-wicket for one.
Length and on off, this is knocked down to long on for another single.
This is pushed through, full and just outside off. This one stays low. Michael Bracewell gets pinged on his back leg.
Flighted and quicker, outside off, turning in a touch. Michael Bracewell tries to have a poke at it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Full and on middle. Michael Bracewell tucks it to mid-wicket by using the depth of his crease. One taken.
Mir Hamza bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Michael Bracewell defends this towards cover.
Goes slightly fuller this time and gets some shaped away, outside off. Michael Bracewell dabs this towards point.
Continues to bowl full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell mistimes his shot back towards the bowler.

Strays onto the pads this time on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell flicks this towards deep square leg and collects two runs. Had he missed the ball it would have hit him on the pads right in front of the stumps.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off. Michael Bracewell gets across the line and punches this towards mid on.
This is short as well and wide outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell is content with leaving this one alone.
Abrar Ahmed bowls this full and outside off, quicker in the air. Tom Blundell punches this towards cover.
Angles this onto the pads on a shorter length. Tom Blundell clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Floats this one full and on an off stump line. Michael Bracewell goes deep in the crease and dabs this towards short leg.
Flighted full and outside off. Michael Bracewell goes for the reverse sweep but hit it to the right of backward point. They take a single though.
This is slightly short and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell rocks back and works this wide of mid on for a single.
A loopy delivery bowled full and outside off, Michael Bracewell takes a good stride forward and smothers this into the pitch.
Naseem Shah starts off this spell with a fullish delivery outside off. Tom Blundell looks to flick this into the leg side but hits it straight to mid-wicket.
Goes full once again and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell gets forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Fires this one full and angles this into the stumps. Tom Blundell clips this ball wide of mid on for a quick single.
Continues to bowl full and angles this away from just outside off. Michael Bracewell knocks this towards cover.

FOUR! Hit uppishly but races away to the fence! Naseem Shah goes full once again and wider outside off. Michael Bracewell skews this off the outer edge of his bat towards deep backward point for four runs.
Goes 'round the wicket now and angles this into the left-handed batter on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell gets behind this and blocks it solidly to cover.
Agha Salman starts off with a loopy delivery bowled in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell shimmies down the wicket and clips this to short mid-wicket.
Bowls this full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell looks to play this into the off side but gets an inside edge to fine leg for a single.
Floats this one full and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell is watchful as he leaves this one alone.
Flighted full and angled into the stumps. Michael Bracewell looks to paddle this fine but does not connect well enough.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell dabs this towards point.
Fires this one full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell goes for the reverse sweep and gets this to deep backward point for a couple of runs.

NO BALL AND LEG BYE! Naseem Shah bowls this back of a length and going down leg. Michael Bracewell looks to pull but misses and the ball goes off the waist towards fine leg for a leg bye. The umpire spots the bowler cut the side line of the crease and indicates a no ball.
Goes full this time and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell shuffles down the wicket and flicks this towards mid on.
Continues bowling full and outside the off pole. Tom Blundell gets across the stumps and clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Comes 'round the wicket to the southpaw and serves this full, angled into the stumps. Michael Bracewell tucks this towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short this time and into the batter. Michael Bracewell gets on his toes and works this towards deep square leg for one.

That is FIFTY for Tom Blundell! He has bailed his team out of a spot of bother. Naseem Shah bowls this full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell looks to play this into the offside but gets an inside edge onto his pads. The ball does roll to cover and they rush across for a single.
Bowls this one on a good length and just outside off. Michael Bracewell defends this solidly to the cover fielder.
Fuller and on leg. Blundell nudges it to mid-wicket.
Tom Blundell dances down the track, turns it into a full delivery and whips it to short mid-wicket.
A single now as this is knocked down to long on for a single.
This is flatter, outside off. Michael Bracewell looks to chase it but misses.
This is pushed through, outside off. Michael Bracewell blocks it to the off side.
It is full and on the pads, Michael Bracewell flicks it to square leg for a single. He will retain the strike here. These two seem to be in good touch now.
Much fuller, on off. Michael Bracewell knocks it down to mid on.
This full delivery is tucked towards mid on but straight to the fielder.
Good length, wide of off, angled in. Michael Bracewell dabs it to backward point for a single.
This is full, tailing back into the pads. Tom Blundell clips it to the left of mid on.
It is a good-length ball, in the channel, turning away a touch. Tom Blundell defends it off his back foot to point.
This is full, swinging down leg. Tom Blundell rocks back and flicks it off his pads to mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Incredible shot. It is a short ball, outside off. Tom Blundell goes back and punches it through covers for a cracking boundary.
Short again, on middle. Tom Blundell pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Michael Bracewell cuts it past backward point. They take two runs.
It is pushed through quicker, full and on off. Tom Blundell clips it to the leg side.
This is flicked through square leg off his pads for one run.
Flatter and quicker, wide of off. Michael Bracewell looks to have a poke at it but misses it completely.
Fuller, sliding down leg. Blundell nudges it past short leg.
Another dot. Full and wide of off. Tom Blundell prods and defends it out.
On middle and leg. Tom Blundell steps forward and blocks it to the leg side.
It is full length, on the stumps. Blundell comes down the track and whips it to short mid-wicket.
On off, blocked out.

Ahmed goes slower through the air this time, outside off, this one turns in a long way. Tom Blundell decides to leave this one and is fortunate enough to not see the ball crash into the off pole. Sarfaraz Ahmed still cannot believe how that missed the stumps.
Looped up, outside off. Bracewell knocks it to cover.
Darted on the pads, clipped to fine leg.
This one barely stays up after hitting the deck. Michael Bracewell digs it out late.
Around off, defended out.
Full, on off. Michael Bracewell remains solid in his defense.
A maiden for Salman now, as Michael Bracewell defends it out watchfully.
Abrar Ahmed bowls this full and angling down leg. The ball skids through and Tom Blundell misses his flick to get hit on the pads.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell knocks this towards cover.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside off. Tom Blundell rocks back and punches this to cover.
This is short as well and in line with the stumps. Tom Blundell tucks this towards deep square leg for a single
Goes full once again and pitches this on leg stump. Michael Bracewell blocks this towards mid-wicket.

Signs of aggression from Michael Bracewell! Abrar Ahmed floats this full and outside off. Michael Bracewell charges down the wicket and looks to loft this over mid off. Slices the ball and just manages to clear the fielder for two runs.
Agha Salman bowls this full and into the stumps. Tom Blundell is down the wicket and flicks this to deep square leg for a single.
Floats this one full and outside off. Michael Bracewell pushes at it and is beaten.
This is wide outside off on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell leaves this one alone.
Tosses this in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell defends this back down the pitch.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off. Michael Bracewell blocks this into the off side.

Fires this one full and angling down leg, Michael Bracewell misses his flick Sarfaraz Ahmed collects the ball before whipping the bails off. The go upstairs to check for a stumping but Michael Bracewell is well in the crease.
Full and on leg, defended to short leg.
Pushed through quicker and in line with the stumps. Blundell gets an inside edge on his pads.
Loopy delivery bowled full and oustide off. Tom Blundell defends this back down the wicket.
Bowls this slightly short and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell eases this off the back foot to mid on.
Flights this full and outside off. Tom Blundell blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Angled into the stumps on a fuller length. Tom Blundell defends this towards short leg.
Angles this into the stumps on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell defends this back down the pitch.
Goes full once again and into the stumps. Michael Bracewell knocks this back towards the bowler.

Flights this one full and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell strokes this towards deep backward point and they take three runs. Tom Blundell pulls up though after the third run and this does not look good.
Agha Salman tosses this full and just outside off. Tom Blundell clips this towards short mid-wicket.
This is slightly short and outside off. Tom Blundell goes deep in the crease and whips this towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Tom Blundell looks to play this late but gets an inside edge just past the stumps.
Abrar Ahmed loops this full and into the pads. Michael Bracewell taps this into the pitch.
What a jaffa! Gets this across the batter on a fuller length. Michael Bracewell pushes at this and gets beaten by the extra bounce.
Flights this one full and outside off. Michael Bracewell blocks this towards cover.

FOUR! Too short and it has been dealt with! Abrar Ahmed pulls his length back and serves this outside off. Michael Bracewell transfers his weight on the back foot and thumps this towards deep cover for four runs.
A loopy delivery full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell pushes at this on the front foot and gets an inside edge onto his pads.
This is full as well and in line with the stumps. Michael Bracewell flicks this straight to the mid on fielder.
Floats it up, full and on leg. Blundell nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter and on off, defended out solidly by Tom Blundell.
Flicks this full ball to mid-wicket but finds the fielder.
On middle and leg, tucked to the leg side once again.
It is much fuller, on middle. Tom Blundell tucks it to fine leg for one.
This is tossed up, wide of off. Michael Bracewell looks to go after it but decides against it in the end.
Full, just outside off, blocked.
LEG BYE! Fuller ball, into the pads, Blundell misses his flick and it goes off the pads to square leg for a leg bye.

FOUR! Excellent use of the feet here. Michael Bracewell moves to 49 with this boundary. It is tossed up, full and on middle. Michael Bracewell comes down the track and flicks it to over mid-wicket for four runs.
FOUR! FIFTY FOR BRACEWELL! He started off cautiously but is looking in some great touch now. This is short, outside off, Michael Bracewell goes back and crunches it through covers for four runs.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Michael Bracewell taps this towards point for a single.
Loops it up, on off, blocked out.
Outside off, tapped away to safety.
Fraction short and wide outside off. Michael Bracewell pushes it to cover but straight to the fielder.
A low full toss, Michael Bracewell helps it to mid on.
Agha Salman bowls this full and outside off. Michael Bracewell knocks this towards cover.
Loops this one full and outside the off pole. Michael Bracewell pushes at this and gets beaten.
Tosses this one full and into the stumps. Michael Bracewell defends this towards mid on.
Floated and full, around off. Blundell gets it to the off side.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
SIX! HUGE! Tom Blundell is taking on the spinner here. It is tossed up, on off. Tom Blundell gets low and slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
FOUR! Incredible shot! It is pushed through quicker and full, on off. Tom Blundell paddles it fine. It races away.
This full ball is reverse swept through point for one.
FOUR! What a stunning shot! The runs are coming in thick and fast now. It is full and on off. Michael Bracewell gets low and reverse sweeps it past backward point for four runs.

OUT! CAUGHT! Agha Salman finally finds the breakthrough here. Tom Blundell remains in his aggressive mode but holes out this time. It is tossed up, full and on off. Tom Blundell gets low and smokes it to deep mid-wicket. Imam-ul-Haq settles under it and takes a sharp catch. New Zealand have half of their side back in the hut now. They lead by 296 runs. Still no sign of declaration as it looks like Daryl Mitchell is ready to come on.
Howout: c Imam-ul-Haq b Agha Salman

Commentary: It is full and on off. Daryl Mitchell reverse sweeps it to deep point and gets a single.
Flatter and outside off. Michael Bracewell taps it to point and crosses for a quick single.
Daryl Mitchell once again reverse-sweeps this full ball past backward point for one.
A short ball, outside off, turning away a bit. Michael Bracewell rocks back and looks to cut it away. He gets a thick edge on it but Sarfaraz Ahmed is unable to hold on to it.
Full ball, on off. Michael Bracewell knocks it down to long on for one.
FOUR! Deft touch! Ali dishes it full, outside off. Michael Bracewell waits for it and steers it through the gap between gully and slip cordon for four runs.
A good-length ball, outside off. Michael Bracewell comes down the track and punches it to cover.
Length and on off. Bracewell pushes it into covers and scampers across for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Daryl Mitchell rides the bounce and strokes it towards long on. Single taken.

Overthrows! Back of a length, around off. Michael Bracewell smacks it down the ground. It hits Daryl Mitchell on its way and goes to mid on. The battrs call for one. The throw at the keeper's end is wayward which allows the batter to take another single.
FOUR! Excellent shot! It is a short ball, on off. Michael Bracewell swivels and pulls it along the ground to cow corner. The ball gets into the ropes.
Agha Salman floats this full and in line with the stumps. Daryl Mitchell shimmies down the wicket and clips this to long on for a single.
This is short and wide outside off. Mir Hamza makes room and slashes hard at the ball. Slices this to fine leg for three runs.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Daryl Mitchell taps this towards slip.
Toss this one full and into the stumps. Daryl Mitchell clips this to square leg and looks for a single but there is none.
Flights this full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell goes for the reverse sweep and gets this to third man for a couple of runs.

Missed stumping chance! Agha Salman loops this full and outside off. Daryl Mitchell charges down the wicket and takes a wild swing but misses. The ball goes over the stumps and Sarfaraz Ahmed fumbles with the ball. This allows Daryl Mitchell to get back into the crease and another chance goes begging. Tim Southee has seen enough and calls his players back in.
Tim Southee bowls a good-length delivery outside the off stump and gets it to nip back in. Abdullah Shafique is watchful and leaves this one alone.

OUT! TIMBER! Huge wicket for New Zealand! This is what the visitors would have been hoping for as they draw first blood just before the close of play! This is bowled on a good length and on an off stump line. The ball keeps really low and goes under the bat of Abdullah Shafique as he looks to block it. The stumps are shattered and Pakistan will be slightly worried here as their opener makes his way back to the pavilion.
Howout: b Tim Southee

Commentary: This is on a good length and in line with the stumps. Mir Hamza blocks this solidly back towards the bowler.
Bowls this on slightly outside off on a good length. Mir Hamza knocks this into the off side.
Delivers this one back of a length and in line with the stumps. Mir Hamza stands tall and defends this back down the pitch.
Goes 'round the wicket now and serves this outside off on a good length. Mir Hamza is happy to leave this one alone. Maiden wicket for Tim Southee to start off.
Good length, on off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks it to the leg side.
This is outside off, left alone.
Fuller, in length, on off, blocked out.
A length ball, wide of off. Imam-ul-Haq has no shot to offer.
This is spilled down leg. Imam-ul-Haq misses to glance it around the corner.
Much fuller, on off. Imam-ul-Haq knocks it to mid off. Pakistan are still left to get off the mark.
Angled across, outside off. Hamza prods and defends it to silly point.
Floated and full, on off. Hamza blocks it on his front foot.
Three dots on the trot! Fuller, on off pole. Hamza presses forward and defends it out. Hamza has three more ball to survive.
Sodhi comes 'round the wicket. Goes full and outside off. Hamza gets an inside edge on the pad.

OUT! CLEANED UP! Ish Sodhi makes sure that his side ends the day on a high. Pakistan lose their second wicket and Mir Hamza is unable to protect his wicket. The change of angle does wonders for Ish Sodhi. It is pushed through quicker, full and outside off. It skidds through and comes in with the arm. Mir Hamza prods and tries to defend it out on his front foot. He gets beaten on the inside edge and the ball goes on to shatter the stumps. PAKISTAN ARE 0/2 AT STUMPS ON DAY 4.
Howout: b Ish Sodhi

Commentary: Ish Sodhi floats this full and outside the off stump. Shan Masood blocks this out towards silly point.
Matt Henry starts off from 'round the wicket and serves the full, angled into the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq punches this back towards the bowler who does well to get down on his left and stop the ball.

EDGED AND FOUR! Matt Henry bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq pushes at it and gets a thick edge that flies between the first and second slip for four runs to third man.
On a good length but straying onto the pads. Imam-ul-Haq clips this to deep backward square leg and collects two runs.
Bowls this a touch fuller and in line with the stumps. Imam-ul-Haq defends the back to the bowlers left.
FOUR! This has been stroked away in style! Matt Henry goes full and outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq drives this to deep cover for the second boundary of the over.
This is on a good length and outside the off stump. Imam-ul-Haq taps this into the off side.
Tim Southee also begins from 'round the wicket and serves this a fraction full, outside off. Shan Masood pushes this firmly towards mid off.

Bowls this slightly back of a length and outside the off stump, angling into the batter. Shan Masood gets across the line of the ball to defend but gets squared up. The ball hits the back leg and there is a huge appeal for the bowler. The impact is outside the line of the stumps.
This is on a good length as well and in line with the stumps. Shan Masood taps this back towards the bowler.
Delivers this one outside the off pole and on a good length. Shan Masood dabs this towards the short cover fielder.
BEATEN! Tim Southee gets this to nip away slightly from a good length, outside off. Shan Masood feels for this one and gets beaten.
Continues bowling on a good length outside the off stump. Shan Masood gets across the stumps and leaves this one alone. A maiden over to start off for Tim Southee.

Matt Henry is back over the wicket as he serves this on a good length and just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq strokes this firmly back down the pitch and the bowler sticks his right hand out to stop the ball.
This is on a good length as well and on a leg stump line. Imam-ul-Haq clips this towards mid wicket.
Straying onto the pads on a good length. Imam-ul-Haq manages to tuck this towards backward square leg and collects a single.
Goes 'round the wicket to Shan Masood and serves this one a good length outside off. The batter blocks this out towards cover.
This is a touch fuller and outside the off stump. Shan Masood knocks this towards mid off.

FOUR! Times this one to perfection! Matt Henry continues to bowl full and offers width outside off. Shan Masood gets a good stride forward and cover drives this to the right of mid off for four runs. He is off the mark now.
Tim Southee from 'round the wicket serves this full and just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq gets forward and defends this back towards the bowler.
Continues bowling full and angled in from outside off. Imam-ul-Haq miscues his shot towards the mid on fielder.
Bowls this one wide outside the off stump on a fuller length. Imam-ul-Haq raises his bat and leaves this one alone.
On a good length this time and just outside off. Imam-ul-Haq blocks this solidly towards short cover.
Tosses this one well outside the off pole on a good length. Imam-ul-Haq shoulders his arms to this one.
Continues bowling on a good length and offering width outside off. Imam-ul-Haq leaves this one for the keeper to collect as well.
Matt Henry starts the over with a good-length delivery outside the off pole. Shan Masood punches this to the right of mid on.
Goes a nad bit fuller this time and outside off. Shan Masood gets his front foot forward and knocks this to short cover.
